// Content Sprint 12: Testing and Go-Live.
window.CONTENT_SPRINT_12 = {"testing-strategy":{"summary":"Establish a controlled, risk-based testing programme that defines what the marketplace must prove, who owns each result, how Sandbox and Production are used, what evidence is required, how defects and changes are managed, and when the marketplace may progress to Production Readiness.","audience":["Marketplace leadership","Marketplace operations","Product and ecommerce","Technology and integrations","Catalogue","Finance","Customer service","Seller management","Security","Implementation partners"],"sections":{"Understand Marketplace Testing":"<p>Marketplace testing is a controlled programme that proves the approved operating model across Marketplacer, the ecommerce front end, Seller systems, payment services, fulfilment, customer support and Finance. It is not a collection of unrelated screen checks.</p><div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Start here:</strong> Use this page to plan the programme before executing detailed test cases.</div><h3>Recommended testing sequence</h3><div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Plan the programme</strong><span>Testing Strategy</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Prove the foundation</strong><span>Marketplace Configuration Testing</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Prove the catalogue</strong><span>Catalogue Testing</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Prove the complete transaction</strong><span>End-to-End Testing</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Approve each Seller</strong><span>Seller Launch Readiness</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Approve the marketplace</strong><span>Production Readiness</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Execute the launch</strong><span>Go-Live</span></div></div><p>Workstreams may overlap when their prerequisites are stable. For example, Catalogue Testing can begin for approved Categories while unrelated email configuration is still being finalised. Do not begin a dependent test while the setting or data it relies on is still changing.</p><div class=\"card-grid\"><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Core coverage</h3><p>Configuration, catalogue, payments, Orders, Seller Invoice splitting, fulfilment, tracking, refunds, remittance and recovery.</p></article><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Conditional coverage</h3><p>MConnect, Seller API, Golden Records, wholesale promotional prices, split-funded Promotions or MPay only when they are in scope.</p></article><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Advanced coverage</h3><p>Load, concurrency, complex failure injection and high-volume reconciliation for integrations with material scale or risk.</p></article><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Approval boundary</h3><p>Testing approval means the agreed test scope may enter Production Readiness. It does not approve launch.</p></article></div>","Define Testing Objectives and Success Criteria":"<p>Define what the programme must prove before individual test cases are written. Objectives should be tied to marketplace decisions, customer and Seller obligations, connected-system behaviour and financial outcomes.</p><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Approved marketplace decisions are represented by the correct configuration and integrations.</li><li>Sellers can be created, connected, trained and supported through their actual operating model.</li><li>Products can be ingested, mapped, validated, vetted, published and maintained from the correct source.</li><li>Customers can discover, purchase, receive, cancel or return Products through the approved journey.</li><li>Marketplacer creates one recoverable Order and the correct Seller Invoice split.</li><li>Commission and wholesale models produce the approved Seller entitlement, Operator earnings or margin, tax and fees.</li><li>Marketplacer refund records and the payment-provider cash refund can be reconciled.</li><li>Remittance and payout are explainable and duplicate-safe.</li><li>Failures can be detected, contained and recovered without duplicate Orders, refunds or payouts.</li><li>Business-as-usual teams can operate the marketplace using documented procedures and escalation routes.</li></ul><div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Write measurable success criteria.</strong> Replace statements such as “integration works” with an observable result such as “one Seller Invoice reaches the Seller platform with the correct Line Items and stable source identifier within the agreed time”.</div>","Establish Scope, Assumptions and Exclusions":"<p>Document the exact launch capability represented by the test programme. A scenario that is not in the test scope must not later be described as tested.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Scope dimension</th><th>Record</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Sellers</td><td>Launch Sellers, commercial model, connection and fulfilment method</td></tr><tr><td>Catalogue</td><td>Categories, Product and Variant scope, ingestion methods and Golden Records where used</td></tr><tr><td>Customer journey</td><td>Regions, channels, payment methods, shipping models and Promotions</td></tr><tr><td>Operations</td><td>Cancellation, return, refund, Seller support and Customer Service processes</td></tr><tr><td>Finance</td><td>Tax, Merchant Fees, commission, wholesale, remittance and payout</td></tr><tr><td>Technology</td><td>Storefront, APIs, Webhooks, MConnect, middleware, reporting and monitoring</td></tr><tr><td>Exclusions</td><td>Deferred Sellers, Products, regions, features, integrations or edge cases</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>For each exclusion, record the reason, residual risk, approver, control, revisit date and whether the excluded capability remains technically unavailable to customers and Sellers.</p><div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Do not use “not tested” as an informal workaround.</strong> An untested capability must be removed from launch scope, isolated or treated as a launch blocker.</div>","Prioritise Testing by Marketplace Risk":"<p>Prioritise by potential customer, Seller, financial, privacy and operational impact rather than by how easy a test is to execute.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Risk factor</th><th>Questions</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Customer impact</td><td>Could the customer be charged incorrectly, receive no Order, see the wrong price or lose access to a refund?</td></tr><tr><td>Seller impact</td><td>Could the wrong Seller receive an Invoice, fulfil another Seller’s item or be paid the wrong amount?</td></tr><tr><td>Financial impact</td><td>Could commission, wholesale entitlement, tax, Promotion funding, remittance or payout be wrong?</td></tr><tr><td>Data and privacy</td><td>Could customer or wholesale information reach an unauthorised user, Seller or environment?</td></tr><tr><td>Integration dependency</td><td>How many systems and retries are involved, and can the result be reconciled?</td></tr><tr><td>Recovery difficulty</td><td>Can the team repair the authoritative record without duplication or data loss?</td></tr><tr><td>Volume and frequency</td><td>How often will the scenario occur and how quickly could impact accumulate?</td></tr></tbody></table></div><h3>Highest-priority launch scenarios</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Payment succeeds but no recoverable Marketplacer Order is visible.</li><li>A retry creates a duplicate Order, Seller Order, Shipment, refund or payout.</li><li>Customer price, Seller entitlement or Promotion funding is incorrect.</li><li>Seller source pricing overwrites protected Operator-controlled retail pricing.</li><li>A multi-Seller Order splits incorrectly or exposes another Seller’s information.</li><li>Seller cannot receive or fulfil its Seller Invoice.</li><li>Customer refund cannot be completed or reconciled.</li><li>Remittance or payout cannot be explained.</li><li>Monitoring cannot detect a material failure.</li></ul>","Sequence the Testing Programme":"<p>Run the programme in dependency order. A later test may expose an earlier defect, but foundational work should be stable before the dependent journey is approved.</p><div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><div><strong>Marketplace Configuration Testing</strong><p>Prove settings, permissions, communications, commercial controls, shipping, refunds and integration administration.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><div><strong>Catalogue Testing</strong><p>Prove Product ingestion, structure, Mapping, Catalog Rules, Product Vetting, publication and maintenance.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><div><strong>End-to-End Testing</strong><p>Prove the complete customer, Seller, integration and financial transaction.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><div><strong>Seller Launch Readiness</strong><p>Approve each Seller using evidence from onboarding, catalogue and transaction testing.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><div><strong>Production Readiness</strong><p>Confirm that the approved result exists in Production and conduct the Go or No-Go review.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">6</span><div><strong>Go-Live</strong><p>Activate the approved scope, monitor first live activity, contain issues and transition to BAU.</p></div></div></div><div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Parallel work is allowed.</strong> Run independent workstreams concurrently, but record each page’s entry criteria and block the dependent test until those criteria pass.</div>","Assign Roles, Ownership and Approval Authority":"<p>Testing is cross-functional. A test coordinator manages the programme, but each domain owner must validate and approve the result they will own after launch.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Domain</th><th>Expected owner</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Marketplace configuration</td><td>Marketplace Operations</td></tr><tr><td>Customer experience</td><td>Ecommerce or Product</td></tr><tr><td>Catalogue</td><td>Catalogue team</td></tr><tr><td>Seller operations</td><td>Seller management and participating Seller</td></tr><tr><td>APIs, Webhooks and MConnect</td><td>Technology or Integrations</td></tr><tr><td>Commission and wholesale</td><td>Finance and Commercial</td></tr><tr><td>Payment and customer refunds</td><td>Payments and Finance</td></tr><tr><td>Fulfilment and tracking</td><td>Seller and Marketplace Operations</td></tr><tr><td>Customer support</td><td>Customer Service</td></tr><tr><td>Security and permissions</td><td>Security or platform administrator</td></tr><tr><td>Final business acceptance</td><td>Authorised marketplace leadership</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Every scenario should identify an executor, expected-result owner, evidence owner, defect owner and approver. Avoid one person approving specialist outcomes on behalf of Finance, Technology, Sellers and Customer Service.</p>","Use Sandbox and Production Correctly":"<p>Production is the source of truth and contains live records. Sandbox is the primary environment for broad, repeated and destructive testing.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Use Sandbox for</th><th>Use controlled Production validation for</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Configuration experiments, permission tests and training</td><td>Verifying the approved Production configuration</td></tr><tr><td>Product imports, Mapping, Catalog Rules and Product Vetting</td><td>A small approved live Product and Seller scope</td></tr><tr><td>Repeated Order, cancellation, return and refund scenarios</td><td>One or a small number of controlled transactions</td></tr><tr><td>API, Webhook and MConnect development</td><td>Production credentials, endpoints and monitoring</td></tr><tr><td>Failure injection, duplicate tests and regression</td><td>Live email, payment and payout-provider connectivity</td></tr><tr><td>High-volume or bulk testing</td><td>Smoke testing the approved launch pathway</td></tr></tbody></table></div><h3>Before a Sandbox test cycle</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Confirm when the latest Production-to-Sandbox refresh occurred.</li><li>Confirm test users, Sellers, Products and data still exist.</li><li>Recreate Sandbox Webhooks when they were cleared by refresh.</li><li>Reconnect MConnect where required.</li><li>Verify credentials, email routing and every endpoint points to Sandbox.</li><li>Confirm no Sandbox action can affect a Production Seller, customer or payment account.</li></ul><div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Do not assume Sandbox remains unchanged.</strong> A refresh can replace Sandbox data and remove connections even when the feature under test has not changed.</div>","Prepare Representative Test Data":"<p>Use a compact but realistic data set that represents every material launch pattern. The purpose is coverage, not the largest possible record count.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Test data area</th><th>Representative examples</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Sellers</td><td>Commission Seller, wholesale Seller, manually managed Seller and integrated Seller where applicable</td></tr><tr><td>Products</td><td>Single-Variant, multi-Variant, different Categories, Sale pricing, wholesale pricing and special shipping</td></tr><tr><td>Catalogue states</td><td>Mapped, unmapped, valid, invalid, approved, rejected, online and offline</td></tr><tr><td>Orders</td><td>Single-Seller, multi-Seller, several quantities, different shipping and Promotion funding</td></tr><tr><td>Fulfilment</td><td>Full, partial, split Shipment, invalid tracking and duplicate attempt</td></tr><tr><td>Exceptions</td><td>Payment failure, uncertain outcome, cancellation, return, partial refund and full refund</td></tr><tr><td>Finance</td><td>Commission, wholesale, remittance, payout and post-payout recovery where relevant</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Use recognisable test names, SKUs, External IDs and payment references so records can be traced across the storefront, Marketplacer, Seller systems and Finance tools.</p>","Define Evidence and Traceability Requirements":"<p>Testing is complete only when the expected result, actual result and evidence can be reconstructed by another reviewer.</p><div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Business requirement</strong><span>What the marketplace must achieve</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Configuration or integration control</strong><span>How the requirement is implemented</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Test case</strong><span>How the control is exercised</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Expected result</strong><span>What must happen before execution begins</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Actual result</strong><span>What happened in every system</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Evidence</strong><span>Identifiers, screenshots, logs and calculations</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Defect or approval</strong><span>How the result is resolved and accepted</span></div></div><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Evidence field</th><th>Examples</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Test definition</td><td>Test ID, risk, environment, preconditions, executor and approver</td></tr><tr><td>Marketplacer records</td><td>Seller, Product, Variant, Order, Seller Invoice, Shipment, Refund Request and Remittance Advice IDs</td></tr><tr><td>Connected records</td><td>Storefront Order, payment, Seller platform Order, payout and accounting references</td></tr><tr><td>Financial evidence</td><td>Expected and actual customer amount, commission, Wholesale Price, tax, fees, refund and payout</td></tr><tr><td>Technical evidence</td><td>Request and response, Webhook event, retry, MConnect record, logs and timestamps</td></tr><tr><td>Decision evidence</td><td>Pass, fail, accepted risk, workaround, owner and approval date</td></tr></tbody></table></div><div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Calculate expected financial results first.</strong> Do not use the platform result to define what the platform result was supposed to be.</div>","Manage Defects, Retesting and Regression":"<p>Use one defect register across all test pages so duplicate issues and cross-system impact can be seen together.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Severity</th><th>Guidance</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Critical</td><td>Unsafe to trade, major payment, privacy, duplication or unrecoverable financial risk</td></tr><tr><td>High</td><td>Incorrect price, Seller entitlement, Order routing, fulfilment or refund outcome</td></tr><tr><td>Medium</td><td>Material issue with a controlled and tested workaround</td></tr><tr><td>Low</td><td>Limited usability, content or presentation issue</td></tr></tbody></table></div><h3>Defect record</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Defect ID, environment, test case and failing boundary.</li><li>Expected result, actual result and supporting evidence.</li><li>Customer, Seller, financial, data and operational impact.</li><li>Containment, workaround, owner and target resolution.</li><li>Retest result, related regression scope and closure approver.</li></ul><p>Closing a defect requires the original test to pass and the affected related journeys to pass regression. A commission fix may require retesting Promotions, refunds, remittance and several Commission Package rules.</p>","Control Changes During Testing":"<p>Treat configuration, data, code and integration changes as controlled test events. Every material change should identify which evidence is no longer reliable.</p><h3>High-risk changes</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Finance Settings, tax, Commission Packages, wholesale pricing or Merchant Fees.</li><li>Seller permissions, Remittance Delay, payout approval or Seller commercial model.</li><li>Shipping Profiles, Zones, Rates, Refund Reasons or return permissions.</li><li>Catalog Rules, Product Vetting, Mapping, Product transformations or source ownership.</li><li>Payment configuration, API payloads, Webhooks, MConnect or middleware.</li><li>Customer emails, storefront pricing, checkout or fulfilment logic.</li></ul><p>For each change, record the reason, owner, approver, affected tests, targeted retest, regression scope, evidence updates and whether Production Readiness approval is affected.</p><h3>Release and deprecation check</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Review What’s New on Marketplacer before a major test cycle and before final approval.</li><li>Review the API Change Log and Developer documentation for affected integrations.</li><li>Confirm no deprecated API or legacy Seller API is being introduced for new development.</li><li>Update tests when Webhook retry, deduplication, MConnect, Product, refund or Finance behaviour changes.</li></ul>","Define Entry, Exit and Approval Criteria":"<h3>Before you begin</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list\"><li>Business requirements, decisions, scope and exclusions are documented.</li><li>The required configuration and representative test data exist.</li><li>Test users and connected systems are available in the correct environment.</li><li>Expected outcomes and financial calculations are documented.</li><li>Owners, approvers, evidence storage and defect workflow are ready.</li></ul><h3>This page is complete when</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list\"><li>Every required scenario has been executed and evidenced.</li><li>Commission and wholesale calculations pass where applicable.</li><li>Payments, customer refunds, remittance and payout reconcile.</li><li>Critical and high launch blockers are closed.</li><li>Accepted issues have tested controls, owners and dates.</li><li>Related regression has passed.</li><li>Operational teams can perform the processes they will own.</li><li>Domain owners have formally approved the result.</li></ul><div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Next step:</strong> Continue to <a href=\"?page=configuration-testing\">Marketplace Configuration Testing</a>.</div><div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Approval statement:</strong> The agreed test programme and scope are ready to proceed through the detailed testing pages and ultimately enter Production Readiness. Testing Strategy does not approve launch.</div>","Operator Testing Strategy Checklist":"<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>A test coordinator and domain owners are assigned.</li><li>Launch scope, assumptions and exclusions are approved.</li><li>Risks are prioritised by customer, Seller, financial, privacy and recovery impact.</li><li>The testing sequence and parallel workstreams are documented.</li><li>Sandbox readiness and refresh impacts are checked.</li><li>Representative Sellers, Products, Orders and financial scenarios are prepared.</li><li>Expected results are written before execution.</li><li>Evidence and identifier requirements are agreed.</li><li>One defect register, severity model and closure process are in use.</li><li>Change control and regression rules are agreed.</li><li>Current Support, Developer and Changelog updates are reviewed.</li><li>Entry, exit and approval criteria are recorded.</li></ul><h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"link-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/26318966306957-Staging-environment-sync\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Staging environment sync</a></li><li><a href=\"https://dev.marketplacer.com/docs/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Marketplacer Developer Documentation</a></li><li><a href=\"https://dev.marketplacer.com/docs/changes/changes/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">API Change Log</a></li><li><a href=\"https://dev.marketplacer.com/docs/changes/deprecation-process/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Deprecation Process</a></li><li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/webhooks/webhookretries/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Webhook Retry Policy</a></li><li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/webhooks/deduplication/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Webhook Deduplication</a></li><li><a href=\"https://changelog.marketplacer.com/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">What’s New on Marketplacer</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/requests/new\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Submit a request</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["configuration-testing","Marketplace Configuration Testing"],["catalogue-testing","Catalogue Testing"],["end-to-end-testing","End-to-End Testing"],["seller-launch-readiness","Seller Launch Readiness"],["production-readiness","Production Readiness"],["go-live","Go-Live"]]},"configuration-testing":{"summary":"Confirm that marketplace-wide settings and Seller-specific overrides implement the approved operating model, produce the intended user, Seller, customer and financial outcomes, remain correctly separated across Sandbox and Production, and can be supported safely after launch.","audience":["Marketplace operations","Technology and integrations","Finance","Customer service","Seller management","Catalogue","Ecommerce","Security","Platform administrators"],"sections":{"Understand Marketplace Configuration Testing":"<p>Marketplace Configuration Testing proves that marketplace-wide settings and Seller-specific overrides implement the approved operating model and produce the expected user, Seller, customer, integration and financial outcome.</p><div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Approved decision</strong><span>What the marketplace has agreed</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Marketplacer configuration</strong><span>The marketplace-wide setting</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Seller override</strong><span>The approved exception where applicable</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Resulting workflow</strong><span>The outcome in the Portal, storefront or connected system</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Evidence and approval</strong><span>Proof that the result passed</span></div></div><div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>A selected checkbox is not a passed test.</strong> Exercise the resulting workflow, calculation, permission or communication.</div><h3>Before you begin</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list\"><li>Testing Strategy is approved.</li><li>The configuration register and business decisions exist.</li><li>Sandbox access and post-refresh connections are ready.</li><li>Representative users, Sellers, Products and financial examples are available.</li></ul>","Build the Configuration Register":"<p>Maintain one register for every launch-relevant setting and override.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Record</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Configuration domain</td><td>Site, users, Seller, Product, Finance, shipping, refunds or integrations</td></tr><tr><td>Approved decision</td><td>The business or operating requirement implemented by the setting</td></tr><tr><td>Environment</td><td>Sandbox and Production value</td></tr><tr><td>Level</td><td>Marketplace default or Seller-specific override</td></tr><tr><td>Expected outcome</td><td>What should happen and what should be prevented</td></tr><tr><td>Evidence</td><td>Test case, identifiers and result</td></tr><tr><td>Governance</td><td>Owner, approver, last change and regression impact</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Include Site Details, Customisation, Language Customisation, account emails, SendGrid, authentication, SSO, users, roles, Seller Settings, Advert Settings, Golden Product Settings where used, Finance Settings, Payment Methods, Commission Packages, Promotions, Refund Reasons, Shipping, Carriers, Apps and Integrations, API keys, OAuth clients, Webhooks and Seller Onboarding Processes.</p>","Define the Expected Outcome for Each Setting":"<p>Convert each setting into a positive and negative test.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Configuration</th><th>Outcome to prove</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Marketplace logo</td><td>Correct logo appears in the Seller Portal and Marketplacer-generated emails</td></tr><tr><td>Accounts email</td><td>Finance and remittance communication reaches the monitored recipient</td></tr><tr><td>Seller cancellation permission</td><td>Approved Seller can cancel an eligible pre-dispatch item and a restricted Seller cannot</td></tr><tr><td>Commission Package</td><td>Correct rule and rate are stored against the representative transaction</td></tr><tr><td>Wholesale Seller</td><td>Seller entitlement uses Wholesale Price and does not receive unintended commission</td></tr><tr><td>Remittance Delay</td><td>Completed Seller Invoice remains ineligible until the approved delay has passed</td></tr><tr><td>Shipping Rate</td><td>Eligible customer sees the correct option and an ineligible destination is blocked</td></tr><tr><td>Refund Reason</td><td>Reason appears only in the intended cancellation, return or denial workflow</td></tr><tr><td>Webhook</td><td>Correct event reaches the approved endpoint and duplicate processing is prevented</td></tr></tbody></table></div>","Confirm the Test Environment and Configuration Baseline":"<p>Production is the source of truth. Use Sandbox for repeated, negative and regression testing, then compare the approved result directly with Production.</p><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Confirm the latest Sandbox refresh date.</li><li>Recreate Sandbox Webhooks and MConnect connections after refresh.</li><li>Verify all credentials and endpoints are environment-specific.</li><li>Verify Sandbox email routing and payment accounts cannot affect live users.</li><li>Capture the configuration baseline before testing and after every approved change.</li><li>Document intentional differences between Sandbox and Production.</li></ul><div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Do not aim for accidental environment identity.</strong> Production and Sandbox should implement the same approved operating decisions, but credentials, endpoints, email routing, payments and live data should remain intentionally different.</div>","Test Marketplace Identity and Communications":"<p>Test Site Details, branding and communications as one connected identity system.</p><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Site Name, Site URL, legal name, registration number and addresses.</li><li>Standard Logo, Email Logo and favicon.</li><li>Info, Accounts, Order-copy, remittance-copy, no-reply and Customer Support addresses.</li><li>Language Customisation for Seller, invoice, refund and remittance communications.</li><li>SendGrid whitelabelling and delivery reputation.</li><li>Correct Production links and reply routes.</li></ul><h3>Trigger representative communications</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Operator or Seller invitation and password reset.</li><li>New Seller Invoice notification.</li><li>Product rejection or Catalog Rule message.</li><li>Cancellation, return and refund communication.</li><li>Remittance Advice and payout communication.</li><li>Operational alert or integration failure notification.</li></ul><p>Confirm the correct sender, recipient, identity, Order or Seller information, environment URL, support route and absence of duplicate communication from Marketplacer and connected systems.</p>","Test Authentication, Users and Permissions":"<p>Test allowed and denied actions for local login, MFA, SSO and role-based access.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Role test</th><th>Expected control</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Customer Service</td><td>Can support Orders and refunds but cannot change Finance Settings</td></tr><tr><td>Catalogue</td><td>Can manage Product governance but cannot approve payouts</td></tr><tr><td>Finance</td><td>Can review remittance and payout but cannot create API keys unless authorised</td></tr><tr><td>Technology</td><td>Can manage integrations within approved scope but cannot alter commercial terms</td></tr><tr><td>Restricted user</td><td>Cannot create Full Admin users, manage SSO, change Webhooks or grant itself access</td></tr><tr><td>Inactive user</td><td>Cannot log in or retain a valid session</td></tr></tbody></table></div><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Test invitation, first login, MFA enrolment, recovery codes, password reset and account recovery.</li><li>Test SSO role assignment and update behaviour where used.</li><li>Review implementation-partner and emergency administrator access.</li><li>Confirm high-risk functions that require a local password can be completed by authorised owners.</li></ul>","Test Seller Defaults and Seller-Specific Overrides":"<p>Make marketplace defaults and Seller overrides a core test theme.</p><div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Marketplace default</strong><span>The standard position for a new Seller</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>New Seller</strong><span>Confirm inheritance</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Approved override</strong><span>Apply the documented Seller exception</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Result</strong><span>Confirm only the intended Seller changes</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Regression</strong><span>Confirm unrelated Sellers remain correct</span></div></div><ul class=\"criteria-list\"><li>Commission Package and commercial model.</li><li>Remittance Delay, Merchant Fees and payout approval.</li><li>Fulfilment SLA and operating days.</li><li>Product Vetting, Product permissions and API or MConnect access.</li><li>Cancellation and Seller-initiated refund permissions.</li><li>Notifications, shipping controls, tracking and packing-slip settings.</li></ul><div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Document every override.</strong> Record its business reason, approver, test result and review date so exceptions remain visible after launch.</div>","Test Product and Catalogue Governance Settings":"<p>Test the settings that govern detailed Catalogue Testing.</p><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Available price types and price units.</li><li>Limited-stock threshold.</li><li>Product auto-mapping and Seller access to Mapping.</li><li>Advert Vetting monitored attributes.</li><li>Product Vetting defaults and Seller-level requirement.</li><li>Golden Product Settings where used.</li><li>Catalog Rule and Product approval permissions.</li><li>Seller Product-management and source-ownership controls.</li></ul><p>Confirm that monitored changes return to governance as intended, Sellers cannot bypass required approval, unused features do not create customer behaviour and Golden Record settings affect only marketplaces using that model.</p>","Test Commission, Wholesale and Promotion Configuration":"<h3>Commission</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Commission Packages enabled as approved.</li><li>Default Package and Seller assignment.</li><li>Category, Brand and price-tier rules.</li><li>Rule priority and scheduled changes.</li><li>Commission on postage and refund treatment.</li><li>Resulting Seller entitlement on representative transactions.</li></ul><h3>Wholesale</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Wholesale enabled only for approved Sellers.</li><li>Wholesale Price fields available and populated for live Variants.</li><li>Operator-controlled customer retail pricing remains protected.</li><li>Seller RRP remains reference information.</li><li>Wholesale promotional pricing is governed separately.</li><li>No unintended commission is applied.</li></ul><h3>Promotions</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Eligibility by Seller, Product, Category, customer, date and minimum spend.</li><li>Seller-funded, Operator-funded and split-funded treatment.</li><li>Interaction with commission, wholesale, shipping, tax and refunds.</li><li>Authorised users and source systems can create or change Promotions.</li></ul><div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Commercial models must remain distinct.</strong> A mixed marketplace can support commission and wholesale Sellers, but each transaction must use the correct model and historical values.</div>","Test Tax, Merchant Fees, Remittance and Payout Controls":"<p>Use Finance-approved examples to test each setting and its calculation outcome.</p><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Tax-inclusive or tax-exclusive model and default tax.</li><li>Item, postage, commission and Merchant Fee tax.</li><li>Category, Product or Variant tax overrides and Seller tax registration.</li><li>Tax withholding from Seller remittance.</li><li>Fixed and percentage Merchant Fees and Seller overrides.</li><li>Remittance Delay, schedule, eligibility and manual or automatic approval.</li><li>Manual payout or MPay, payout account, verification, fees and failed-payout process.</li><li>Negative Seller balances, refunds after payout and Finance reconciliation.</li></ul><div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Apply additional approval to one-way or high-risk settings.</strong> Advanced remittances, advanced refunds, advanced amendments, invoice behaviour, automatic payout approval and tax-model decisions require documented ownership, migration impact and rollback limitations.</div>","Test Shipping and Fulfilment Configuration":"<p>Test shipping through configuration and the customer checkout result.</p><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Shipping Profiles assigned to intended Variants.</li><li>Zones, Rates, Rules, free-shipping thresholds and rule priority.</li><li>Seller-managed shipping and flat-rate permissions.</li><li>International, bulky, click-and-collect or special fulfilment where in scope.</li><li>Shipment Carriers and tracking URL construction.</li><li>Marketplace and Seller-specific fulfilment SLAs.</li><li>Return addresses and multiple fulfilment origins where applicable.</li></ul><p>Prove both sides: an eligible Product and destination receive the expected option, while an ineligible Product or destination cannot complete checkout with an invalid Rate.</p>","Test Cancellation, Return and Refund Configuration":"<p>Separate pre-dispatch cancellations, post-dispatch returns and denied requests.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Configuration</th><th>Test</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Pre-dispatch reasons</td><td>Available only for eligible paid and not sent items</td></tr><tr><td>Post-dispatch reasons</td><td>Available for paid and sent items and support return-required or returnless decisions</td></tr><tr><td>Denied reasons</td><td>Record a clear final outcome and remain reportable</td></tr><tr><td>Seller cancellation permission</td><td>Approved Seller can act and restricted Seller cannot</td></tr><tr><td>Seller refund-initiation permission</td><td>Approved Seller can create a post-dispatch request</td></tr><tr><td>Return-label and email settings</td><td>Produce the intended Seller and customer communication</td></tr><tr><td>Invoice and credit-note behaviour</td><td>Produce the approved amendment and Finance record</td></tr></tbody></table></div><div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Marketplacer does not move the customer’s cash by itself.</strong> Test the Marketplacer workflow, payment-provider refund, Seller adjustment and remittance outcome as separate but reconciled controls.</div>","Test Applications, API Keys, OAuth and Webhooks":"<p>Test integration administration, environment separation and operational ownership.</p><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Operator and Seller API keys, owner, scope, storage, rotation and revocation.</li><li>OAuth clients and authentication settings.</li><li>Production and Sandbox endpoints and credentials.</li><li>Webhook object, event, query, headers, enabled state and endpoint.</li><li>Retry, deduplication, rejected, failed and skipped event handling.</li><li>Monitoring, exception queues, alert recipients and reconciliation.</li><li>Removal of obsolete implementation credentials and integrations.</li></ul><h3>Negative tests</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Sandbox key cannot modify Production.</li><li>Production Webhook cannot point to a Sandbox endpoint.</li><li>Unauthorised user cannot create keys or change Webhooks.</li><li>A duplicate event does not repeat the business action.</li><li>A failed or disabled Webhook is visible and recoverable.</li><li>A retry searches for the original transaction before creating another record.</li></ul>","Complete Negative, Change and Regression Testing":"<p>Include at least one negative test for every configuration domain and repeat targeted regression after material changes.</p><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Restricted user cannot approve payout or change high-risk settings.</li><li>Wholesale Product without Wholesale Price cannot become customer-ready.</li><li>Seller source price cannot overwrite protected retail pricing.</li><li>Product without valid shipping cannot complete checkout.</li><li>Invalid Refund Reason cannot be used in the wrong workflow.</li><li>Incorrect environment endpoint is detected before activation.</li><li>Communication does not expose wholesale or confidential information.</li></ul><p>Record each change, approver, affected Sellers and Products, targeted retest, regression scope, Production impact and evidence update.</p>","Define Evidence, Exit Criteria and Approval":"<h3>This page is complete when</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list\"><li>Every launch-relevant decision appears in the configuration register.</li><li>Sandbox configuration and negative tests pass.</li><li>Production differences are documented and controlled.</li><li>Marketplace defaults and Seller overrides are approved.</li><li>Branding, communications, roles and permissions pass.</li><li>Commission, wholesale, tax, fees, remittance and payout controls pass.</li><li>Shipping, refunds, API keys, OAuth and Webhooks pass.</li><li>One-way settings have authorised approval.</li><li>Defects and related regression pass.</li><li>Domain owners approve the results.</li></ul><div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Next step:</strong> Continue to <a href=\"?page=catalogue-testing\">Catalogue Testing</a>.</div><div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Approval statement:</strong> Marketplace configuration has passed the agreed test scope and is ready to support Catalogue Testing, End-to-End Testing and Production Readiness.</div><h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"link-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360037668712-Site-Details\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Site Details</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/25930591592973-Seller-settings\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Seller Settings</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/31441597254285-Finance-Settings\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Finance Settings</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/28925785268365-Operator-user-role-permissions\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Operator user role permissions</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/10549432905229-Manage-single-sign-on-SSO-Identity-Providers\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Manage SSO Identity Providers</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/26318966306957-Staging-environment-sync\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Staging environment sync</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360057263531-Set-up-your-commission-packages\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Set up commission packages</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360055724771-Setting-merchant-fees\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Setting Merchant Fees</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360040011851-Enable-and-use-the-returns-module\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Enable and use the returns module</a></li><li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/operator-api/examples/utility/howto_managewebhooks/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Manage Webhooks</a></li><li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/webhooks/webhookretries/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Webhook Retry Policy</a></li><li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/webhooks/errorsfaults/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Errors and Faults for Webhooks</a></li><li><a href=\"https://changelog.marketplacer.com/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">What’s New on Marketplacer</a></li></ul>","Operator Configuration Testing Checklist":"<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Configuration register is complete and environment-specific.</li><li>Expected positive and negative outcomes are written for each setting.</li><li>Post-refresh Sandbox connections and credentials are verified.</li><li>Marketplace identity, SendGrid and representative communications pass.</li><li>Local login, MFA, SSO, roles and denied permissions pass.</li><li>New Seller defaults and approved overrides pass.</li><li>Product governance settings pass.</li><li>Commission, wholesale and Promotion configuration pass.</li><li>Tax, Merchant Fees, remittance and payout controls pass.</li><li>Shipping, cancellation, return and refund configuration pass.</li><li>API keys, OAuth clients and Webhooks pass.</li><li>High-risk settings have authorised approval.</li><li>Changes are retested and regression is complete.</li><li>Configuration approval is recorded.</li></ul>"},"related":[["testing-strategy","Testing Strategy"],["catalogue-testing","Catalogue Testing"],["end-to-end-testing","End-to-End Testing"],["default-seller-configuration","Default Seller Configuration"],["configuration-overview","Configuration Overview"],["production-readiness","Production Readiness"]]},"catalogue-testing":{"summary":"Confirm that Seller Products and Variants can be ingested through every approved method, aligned to the marketplace taxonomy, validated against Product standards, reviewed through the approved governance workflow, maintained from the correct source and published accurately to the customer experience.","audience":["Catalogue teams","Marketplace operations","Seller management","Ecommerce","Technology and integrations","Commercial","Finance","Participating Sellers"],"sections":{"Understand Catalogue Testing":"<p>Catalogue Testing proves the complete Seller-product lifecycle from source data through ingestion, structure, Mapping, validation, approval, publication, updates and removal.</p><div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Seller source</strong><span>Product and Variant data</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Ingestion</strong><span>Portal, spreadsheet, MConnect, API or feed</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Mapping</strong><span>Seller terminology to marketplace taxonomy</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Validation</strong><span>Catalog Rules and required data</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Product Vetting</strong><span>Operator approval</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Publication</strong><span>Storefront discovery and purchase readiness</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Maintenance</strong><span>Updates, deactivation and recovery</span></div></div><div class=\"callout note\"><strong>This page tests outcomes, not setup instructions.</strong> Use Product Model, Product Ingestion, Bulk Product Management, MConnect, Mapping, Catalog Rules, Product Vetting and Golden Records for the detailed procedures.</div><h3>Before you begin</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list\"><li>Testing Strategy and applicable configuration tests have passed.</li><li>Approved taxonomy, Prototypes, Option Types and Brands exist.</li><li>Representative Sellers, Product sources and storefront connection are available.</li><li>Field ownership and Product governance decisions are documented.</li></ul>","Define Catalogue Scope and Entry Criteria":"<p>Record launch Sellers, ingestion methods, Categories, Brands, Products, Variants, commercial models, shipping, tax, Promotions, restricted Product requirements, Golden Records and deferred assortment.</p><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Confirm every launch Category has the intended Prototype.</li><li>Confirm required Advert and Variant Option Types and Values exist.</li><li>Confirm Product Vetting and Catalog Rule decisions are implemented.</li><li>Confirm each Seller account and Product connection is available.</li><li>Confirm customer storefront or API can receive representative Product data.</li><li>Keep deferred and restricted Products outside the approved test and launch scope.</li></ul>","Build the Catalogue Test Matrix":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Dimension</th><th>Representative coverage</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Seller</td><td>Commission, wholesale and materially different Seller models</td></tr><tr><td>Product structure</td><td>Single-Variant and multi-Variant</td></tr><tr><td>Ingestion</td><td>Seller Portal, Single Sheet, Multi Sheet, MConnect, Seller API, feed or middleware</td></tr><tr><td>Taxonomy</td><td>Several leaf Categories, Prototypes and attribute sets</td></tr><tr><td>Pricing</td><td>Base, Sale, wholesale and promotional wholesale values</td></tr><tr><td>Stock and shipping</td><td>In stock, low stock, zero stock, replenishment and special shipping</td></tr><tr><td>Governance</td><td>Valid, invalid, mapped, unmapped, approved and rejected</td></tr><tr><td>Maintenance</td><td>Update, add Variant, remove Variant, recategorise and deactivate</td></tr><tr><td>Customer result</td><td>Search, filters, Product page, Variant selection and availability</td></tr><tr><td>Recovery</td><td>Failed import, stale data, incorrect Mapping and source correction</td></tr></tbody></table></div><div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Do not test one easy Product only.</strong> The matrix must represent the catalogue patterns and risks that will exist at launch.</div>","Prepare Representative Sellers, Products and Source Data":"<ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>One single-Variant Product and one multi-Variant Product.</li><li>Several buyer-selectable Option Values and required Product attributes.</li><li>One Product in each high-priority launch Category.</li><li>A known Brand and a new or unmapped Brand.</li><li>A correct Mapping suggestion, an incorrect suggestion and no suggestion.</li><li>Products that pass and intentionally fail high-risk Catalog Rules.</li><li>An approved Product that later changes a monitored field.</li><li>Standard, Sale, commission, wholesale and wholesale promotional values where applicable.</li><li>Zero stock, replenishment, special shipping and source removal.</li><li>A duplicate or matching Product where Golden Records are used.</li></ul><p>Use unique SKUs, barcodes and External IDs so each Product and Variant can be traced across the Seller source, Marketplacer and storefront.</p>","Test Product Structure, Taxonomy and Attributes":"<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Leaf Category</strong><span>Correct marketplace classification</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Prototype</strong><span>Required Product and Variant attributes</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Product</strong><span>Shared title, description, Brand and images</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Variants</strong><span>SKU, barcode, stock, price, shipping and buyer-selectable Options</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Customer experience</strong><span>Correct selection, filters and display</span></div></div><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Product is assigned to the correct leaf Category.</li><li>Category uses the intended Prototype.</li><li>Required Product attributes and Variant Options appear.</li><li>Option Values are valid and Variant combinations are unique.</li><li>Each Product has at least one valid Variant.</li><li>SKU, barcode, stock and price belong to the correct Variant.</li><li>Images belong to the intended Product or Variant.</li><li>A Category change applies the new attribute requirements without corrupting the Product.</li></ul>","Test Each Product-Ingestion Method":"<p>For every launch ingestion method, test creation, update, stock, price, Variant addition, Variant removal, deactivation, failure, correction, retry, monitoring and reconciliation.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Method</th><th>Catalogue outcome to prove</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Seller Portal</td><td>Seller can create and correct a compliant Product and Variants.</td></tr><tr><td>Bulk spreadsheet</td><td>Workbook creates and updates records without changing protected IDs.</td></tr><tr><td>MConnect</td><td>Controlled source scope synchronises the approved fields and states.</td></tr><tr><td>Seller API</td><td>Current GraphQL API creates and updates Products with stable identifiers and clear errors.</td></tr><tr><td>Feed or middleware</td><td>Schema, delivery, partial failure, retries and duplicate prevention are controlled.</td></tr></tbody></table></div>","Test Bulk Product Management":"<h3>Test both workflows</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Add new products for new Product and Variant creation.</li><li>Manage product information for updates, enrichment and adding Products or Variants in existing Categories.</li></ul><h3>Single Sheet</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Category and Brand dropdowns work.</li><li>Attribute values entered manually match marketplace reference data exactly.</li><li>Large price, stock, SKU, External ID and visibility changes work.</li><li>Filters, formulas and macros do not alter system identifiers.</li></ul><h3>Multi Sheet</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Category tabs, Brand, Shipping Profile and attribute dropdowns work.</li><li>Missing Category workflow assigns uncategorised Products.</li><li>New Products and Variants can be added in the intended Category.</li></ul><h3>Required controls</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list\"><li>Enter <span class=\"code-pill\">new</span> in the Ad ID column for a new Product.</li><li>Enter <span class=\"code-pill\">variant</span> directly below the Product for a new Variant.</li><li>Treat values as case-sensitive and leave new Variant ID blank.</li><li>Keep mandatory fields populated.</li><li>Use <span class=\"code-pill\">DELETE_VALUE</span> only to clear optional values.</li><li>Use public image URLs and the same upload workflow that generated the workbook.</li><li>Download, correct and re-upload the error workbook without recreating successful rows.</li></ul>","Test Mapping, Reuse and Remapping":"<p>Test Category, Brand, Advert Option Type and Value, and Variant Option Type and Value Mapping.</p><div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Seller source value</strong><span>The Seller terminology</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Suggested Mapping</strong><span>AI or rules-based suggestion</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Review</strong><span>Operator or authorised Seller decision</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Confirmed value</strong><span>Marketplace taxonomy value</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Reuse</strong><span>Future matching source values use the Mapping</span></div></div><ul class=\"criteria-list\"><li>Correct suggestion, incorrect suggestion and no suggestion.</li><li>Manual Mapping and remapping.</li><li>Several source values mapped to one marketplace value.</li><li>New source value introduced after initial onboarding.</li><li>Repeated Product reuses the confirmed Mapping.</li><li>Ambiguous values and broad source Categories are reviewed.</li><li>Incorrect Category Mapping does not silently publish with the wrong required attributes.</li></ul><div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>A suggestion is not an approval.</strong> Review source context, Product details and customer impact before confirming high-risk mappings.</div>","Test Catalog Rules and Validation":"<p>Catalog Rules should prevent avoidable data-quality failures before Product Vetting.</p><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Product title, description, image, image dimensions and format.</li><li>Price, Wholesale Price, tax, Shipping Profile and Variant count.</li><li>SKU and barcode presence or uniqueness.</li><li>Variant image, price, tax and shipping fields.</li><li>Category-specific, regulated or restricted Product requirements.</li></ul><p>For every rule, test valid, missing, boundary and invalid values; Product and Variant result; Seller-visible error; correction at the authoritative source; and successful resubmission.</p><h3>Change scenarios</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Create a new rule against existing Products.</li><li>Edit or disable a rule.</li><li>Apply a Category-specific rule.</li><li>Export failing Products.</li><li>Confirm Sellers can see the rules and understand the errors.</li></ul>","Test Product Vetting and Approved Product Changes":"<ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Seller with Product Vetting enabled and Seller without it.</li><li>Individual and controlled bulk approval.</li><li>Rejection with a usable reason.</li><li>Seller correction and resubmission.</li><li>Approved Product publication and rejected Product remaining offline.</li><li>Authorised and unauthorised approvers.</li><li>Change to title, description, image, Brand, Category, price, Wholesale Price or shipping after approval.</li><li>Review, retain or reject the monitored change.</li></ul><div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Enabling vetting on an established Seller can affect live Products.</strong> Assess the existing catalogue and customer impact before changing the setting.</div>","Test Product Source of Truth and Update Behaviour":"<p>For every important field, record whether it is controlled by the Seller source, MConnect, Seller API, spreadsheet, Marketplacer, Operator transformation, storefront, Golden Record or enrichment provider.</p><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Source update reaches Marketplacer.</li><li>Destination-only edit is overwritten where expected.</li><li>Protected Operator field is not overwritten.</li><li>Stale or out-of-order update is detected.</li><li>Removed Product and Variant behave correctly.</li><li>Manually enriched content is preserved or intentionally replaced.</li><li>Source migration does not create duplicate Products.</li><li>Operations knows where to correct the data and how to recover.</li></ul><div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Correct the authoritative source.</strong> A temporary Marketplacer edit is not a successful fix when the next sync will reverse it.</div>","Test Pricing and Commercial Product Data":"<h3>Commission Products</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Base and Variant Price, Sale Price, RRP and Promotion eligibility.</li><li>Product page, cart and checkout price remain consistent.</li><li>Historical Order retains the price that applied at purchase.</li></ul><h3>Wholesale Products</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Wholesale Price and Variant Wholesale Price are complete.</li><li>Operator-controlled or Operator-approved customer retail price remains protected.</li><li>Seller RRP remains reference information.</li><li>Wholesale promotional price changes temporary Seller cost only.</li><li>Internal wholesale values are not exposed to customers.</li><li>Missing Wholesale Price is blocked or controlled.</li><li>No unintended commission is applied.</li></ul><p>End-to-End Testing owns the full commercial calculation. Catalogue Testing proves that the correct values are supplied, governed and published.</p>","Test Stock, Shipping, Tax and Publication Eligibility":"<p>Confirm every purchasable Variant has valid stock, customer price, tax, Shipping Profile, governance state, required attributes, image and Seller state.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Scenario</th><th>Expected result</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Initial stock</td><td>Marketplacer and storefront availability match the approved source</td></tr><tr><td>Zero stock</td><td>Customer cannot purchase according to the approved experience</td></tr><tr><td>Replenishment</td><td>Product returns to availability without duplicate records</td></tr><tr><td>Stock buffer</td><td>Customer availability reflects the configured buffer</td></tr><tr><td>Invalid Shipping Profile</td><td>Variant remains unavailable for checkout</td></tr><tr><td>Unsupported destination</td><td>No invalid Rate is returned</td></tr><tr><td>Missing tax or required field</td><td>Product does not progress incorrectly</td></tr><tr><td>Product approved but all Variants unavailable</td><td>Customer experience remains clear and not misleading</td></tr></tbody></table></div>","Test Customer-Facing Publication and Discovery":"<ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Approved Products reach the storefront and intended navigation.</li><li>Search, Category placement, Brand and filters are correct.</li><li>Product information, images and Seller attribution are correct.</li><li>Variants and buyer-selectable Options work.</li><li>Unavailable Variants are handled correctly.</li><li>Retail, Sale and Promotion display is correct.</li><li>Stock and shipping information are accurate.</li><li>Wholesale and internal financial information are not exposed.</li><li>Rejected, unmapped, invalid, deferred, restricted and zero-stock Products remain unavailable as designed.</li></ul><p>The Marketplacer taxonomy and storefront navigation may differ, but the front-end transformation must produce the approved customer discovery experience.</p>","Test Golden Records and Duplicate Management Where Used":"<div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Conditional:</strong> Complete this section only when Golden Records or the Central Product Database are used.</div><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Golden Product and Golden Variant structure.</li><li>Seller Product linked by approved barcode or identifier.</li><li>Multiple Seller offers with shared content and Seller-specific price and stock.</li><li>One Seller out of stock or removed.</li><li>Variant overlap, mismatch and duplicate barcode.</li><li>Central content update and Seller-offer update.</li><li>Customer offer selection or Buy Box logic.</li><li>Product-detail-page resolution from the Golden identifier.</li></ul><p>Where Golden Records are not used, mark this Not Applicable and test duplicate detection under the individual Seller Product model.</p>","Reconcile Catalogue Counts, Evidence and Defects":"<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Seller source Products</strong><span>Expected source count</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Imported</strong><span>Marketplacer records</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Mapped</strong><span>Marketplace taxonomy complete</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Valid</strong><span>Catalog Rules passed</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Vetted</strong><span>Approved assortment</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Online</strong><span>Eligible Marketplacer records</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Storefront</strong><span>Customer-visible Products</span></div></div><p>Repeat reconciliation at Product and Variant level. Record expected and actual counts for rejected, unmapped, invalid, offline, zero-stock, duplicate, deferred and storefront records. Every unexplained difference becomes a defect or approved exclusion.</p><h3>Recovery scenarios</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Failed spreadsheet or partial import.</li><li>MConnect disabled or stale.</li><li>API validation error.</li><li>Missing Category or Brand.</li><li>Incorrect Mapping.</li><li>Catalog Rule failure or Product rejection.</li><li>Source Product removed.</li><li>Protected price overwritten.</li><li>Duplicate Product or lost image.</li><li>Unexpected publication or takedown.</li></ul>","Define Exit Criteria and Approval":"<h3>This page is complete when</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list\"><li>Every launch ingestion method has passed.</li><li>Representative Product structures, taxonomy and attributes pass.</li><li>Mapping and repeated Mapping behaviour pass.</li><li>Catalog Rules, Product Vetting and monitored changes pass.</li><li>Product source ownership and protected fields are proven.</li><li>Commission and wholesale Product values are correct.</li><li>Stock, shipping and tax eligibility are correct.</li><li>Approved Products publish and invalid Products remain unavailable.</li><li>Customer discovery and Variant selection pass.</li><li>Golden Records pass where applicable.</li><li>Product and Variant counts reconcile.</li><li>Critical and high catalogue defects are closed.</li><li>Catalogue, Operations, Ecommerce and Technology approve the result.</li></ul><div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Next step:</strong> Continue to <a href=\"?page=end-to-end-testing\">End-to-End Testing</a>.</div><div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Approval statement:</strong> The approved launch catalogue has passed the agreed Product, ingestion, governance and publication test scope and is ready to support End-to-End Testing and Seller Launch Readiness.</div><h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"link-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/19655643593101-Catalog-rules\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Catalog Rules</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/27467503428237-Reviewing-vetted-and-approved-products-and-variants\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Review changes to approved Products</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360012519092-MConnect-Marketplacer-Integrations\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">MConnect</a></li><li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/seller-api/examples/products/howto_addproducts_latest/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Creating Products with the Seller API</a></li><li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/seller-api/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Seller API</a></li><li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/operator-api/examples/product/howto_golden_record/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Golden Products</a></li><li><a href=\"https://changelog.marketplacer.com/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">What’s New on Marketplacer</a></li></ul>","Operator Catalogue Testing Checklist":"<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Catalogue scope and test matrix are approved.</li><li>Each ingestion method was tested for creation, update, removal, failure and recovery.</li><li>Single Sheet and Multi Sheet workflows pass.</li><li>Product structure, taxonomy, Prototypes and attributes pass.</li><li>Mapping, remapping and reuse pass.</li><li>Catalog Rules and Product Vetting pass.</li><li>Source ownership and protected fields are documented.</li><li>Commission and wholesale Product values are correct.</li><li>Stock, shipping, tax and publication eligibility pass.</li><li>Customer discovery and Variant selection pass.</li><li>Golden Records or duplicate management pass where applicable.</li><li>Catalogue counts reconcile and approval is recorded.</li></ul>"},"related":[["testing-strategy","Testing Strategy"],["configuration-testing","Marketplace Configuration Testing"],["end-to-end-testing","End-to-End Testing"],["product-ingestion","Product Ingestion Methods"],["bulk-product-management","Bulk Product Management"],["mapping","Mapping"],["catalog-rules","Catalog Rules"],["product-vetting","Product Vetting"],["golden-records","Golden Records and Central Product Database"]]},"end-to-end-testing":{"summary":"Validate the complete marketplace journey from customer discovery and checkout through Marketplacer Order creation, Seller fulfilment, cancellations, returns, refunds, commercial calculations, remittance and payout. Test commission and wholesale Sellers separately, include multi-Seller and mixed-model transactions, and prove that failures can be recovered without duplicate Orders, refunds or payouts.","audience":["Marketplace operations","Ecommerce","Product","Technology and integrations","Finance","Customer service","Catalogue","Seller management","Participating Sellers","Implementation partners"],"sections":{"Understand End-to-End Testing":"<p>End-to-end testing proves that the marketplace works as one connected customer, Seller, operational, technical and financial process. It begins before checkout and continues until the transaction, fulfilment, customer outcome, Seller entitlement, remittance, payout and reporting can all be reconciled.</p><div class=\"detail-grid detail-grid-two\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Customer and Seller outcome</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>The customer receives the Product or the correct refund.</li><li>Each Seller receives only its own Seller Invoice and can fulfil it.</li><li>The Seller entitlement and actual payout reconcile.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Operator and Finance outcome</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>The Operator’s commission, revenue or wholesale margin is understood.</li><li>Remittance is approved using the correct historical transaction values.</li><li>Reporting reflects the final transaction and every exception is traceable.</li></ul></article></div><h3>Complete transaction path</h3><div class=\"reconciliation-flow\"><span>Product source</span><b>→</b><span>Marketplacer catalogue</span><b>→</b><span>Operator storefront</span><b>→</b><span>Cart and checkout</span><b>→</b><span>Customer payment</span><b>→</b><span>Marketplacer Order</span><b>→</b><span>Seller Invoice</span><b>→</b><span>Seller fulfilment</span><b>→</b><span>Shipment and tracking</span><b>→</b><span>Cancellation, return or completion</span><b>→</b><span>Commercial calculation</span><b>→</b><span>Remittance and payout</span></div><p>In a connected implementation, the ecommerce platform commonly accepts customer payment and then submits the transaction to Marketplacer through <code class=\"code-pill\">orderCreate</code>. Marketplacer creates the marketplace Order and the Seller-level Invoices required for fulfilment.</p><div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>A storefront confirmation is not a passing result.</strong> Payment, Marketplacer, every participating Seller, fulfilment, Customer Service and Finance must all contain the expected outcome.</div><h3>Before you begin</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Configuration and catalogue prerequisites have passed.</li><li>Representative Sellers and Products are available.</li><li>Payment, Order creation and Seller-delivery paths are operational.</li><li>Finance has calculated the expected commercial results.</li><li>All participating teams and Sellers are available.</li></ul>","Define the Complete Marketplace Journey":"<p>Document the exact journey being tested so every team understands its responsibility and the expected handoff to the next system or team.</p><div class=\"detail-grid detail-grid-two\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Customer journey</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Discover and select the correct Product and Variant.</li><li>Review Seller, delivery, price, Promotion and availability information.</li><li>Complete cart, shipping, checkout and payment.</li><li>Receive Order, Shipment and tracking updates.</li><li>Request cancellation or return where required.</li><li>Receive the Product or the correct refund.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Seller journey</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Create or supply the Product and maintain price and stock.</li><li>Receive the correct Seller Invoice once.</li><li>Fulfil the correct Line Items and quantities.</li><li>Supply Carrier and tracking information.</li><li>Respond to cancellation and return requests.</li><li>Receive and understand remittance and payout records.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Operator journey</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Govern Sellers, Products and customer-facing pricing.</li><li>Monitor Orders, Seller Invoices, fulfilment and tracking.</li><li>Support customers and manage exceptions.</li><li>Validate commission or wholesale calculations.</li><li>Approve remittance and reconcile payout.</li><li>Monitor reporting, incidents and recovery.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Integration journey</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Synchronise Products, prices and stock.</li><li>Create one recoverable Marketplacer Order with stable identifiers.</li><li>Deliver Seller Invoices to the correct Seller systems.</li><li>Return Shipments and tracking.</li><li>Pass refund and financial updates where supported.</li><li>Detect, retry and recover failures without duplication.</li></ul></article></div>","Establish Entry Criteria":"<p>Do not begin formal end-to-end testing until the foundational work has passed. Resolve blocked prerequisites before execution rather than hiding them as end-to-end defects.</p><div class=\"detail-grid detail-grid-two\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Configuration ready</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Operator users, roles and Seller defaults have been tested.</li><li>Commission or wholesale configuration is approved.</li><li>Tax, Merchant Fees and Remittance Delay are approved.</li><li>Shipping and Refund Reasons are configured.</li><li>Customer and Seller communications have been reviewed.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Catalogue ready</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Test Sellers are active.</li><li>Representative Products are ingested and published.</li><li>Mapping, Catalog Rules and Product Vetting have passed.</li><li>Price, stock and Shipping Profiles are correct.</li><li>Storefront Products are available.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Integrations ready</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Storefront connection and payment testing are operational.</li><li><code class=\"code-pill\">orderCreate</code> and stable External IDs are implemented.</li><li>Seller Order delivery and Shipment return paths are operational.</li><li>Required Webhooks are active.</li><li>Monitoring and exception queues are available.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Participants ready</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Test coordinator.</li><li>Marketplace Operations and Ecommerce.</li><li>Technology or Integrations.</li><li>Finance and Customer Service.</li><li>Seller management and participating test Sellers.</li></ul></article></div>","Build the End-to-End Test Matrix":"<p>Build a matrix that covers distinct business and technical journeys rather than repeating one easy transaction.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Scenario</th><th>Sellers</th><th>Commercial model</th><th>Fulfilment outcome</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Standard Order</td><td>One</td><td>Commission</td><td>Full dispatch</td></tr><tr><td>Standard wholesale Order</td><td>One</td><td>Wholesale</td><td>Full dispatch</td></tr><tr><td>Multi-Seller Order</td><td>Two or more</td><td>Commission</td><td>Full dispatch</td></tr><tr><td>Mixed-model Order</td><td>Two or more</td><td>Commission and wholesale</td><td>Full dispatch</td></tr><tr><td>Promotion Order</td><td>One or more</td><td>Applicable model</td><td>Full dispatch</td></tr><tr><td>Partial Shipment</td><td>One</td><td>Either</td><td>Several Shipments</td></tr><tr><td>Pre-dispatch cancellation</td><td>One</td><td>Either</td><td>No dispatch</td></tr><tr><td>Post-dispatch return</td><td>One</td><td>Either</td><td>Returned and refunded</td></tr><tr><td>Partial refund</td><td>One or more</td><td>Either</td><td>Remaining items retained</td></tr><tr><td>Integration recovery</td><td>One or more</td><td>Either</td><td>Recovered without duplication</td></tr></tbody></table></div><h3>Additional variations</h3><div class=\"detail-grid detail-grid-two\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Customer and basket</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Registered and guest customers where supported.</li><li>One or several Variants.</li><li>Quantity greater than one.</li><li>Single-Seller and multi-Seller baskets.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Shipping and fulfilment</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Standard, free and special or bulky shipping.</li><li>Supported and unsupported destinations.</li><li>Full, partial and split fulfilment.</li><li>Tracking and delivery exceptions.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Commercials</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Commission and wholesale Sellers.</li><li>Seller-funded and Operator-funded Promotions.</li><li>Wholesale promotional price.</li><li>Tax and Merchant Fee variations.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Exceptions and recovery</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>No-stock Product.</li><li>Payment failure or timeout.</li><li>Order-creation uncertainty.</li><li>Duplicate event, refund or payout retry.</li></ul></article></div>","Assign Journey Owners":"<p>Each stage needs a named owner.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Journey stage</th><th>Primary owner</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Product presentation</td><td>Ecommerce and Catalogue</td></tr><tr><td>Price and stock</td><td>Commercial, Seller and integrations</td></tr><tr><td>Cart and shipping</td><td>Ecommerce</td></tr><tr><td>Payment</td><td>Payments and Finance</td></tr><tr><td>Marketplacer Order</td><td>Integration team and Operations</td></tr><tr><td>Seller Invoice receipt</td><td>Seller management and Seller</td></tr><tr><td>Fulfilment</td><td>Seller</td></tr><tr><td>Shipment return</td><td>Seller integration and Operations</td></tr><tr><td>Customer communication</td><td>Customer service and Ecommerce</td></tr><tr><td>Refund workflow</td><td>Customer service and Operations</td></tr><tr><td>Payment refund</td><td>Payments and Finance</td></tr><tr><td>Commission or wholesale calculation</td><td>Finance</td></tr><tr><td>Remittance</td><td>Finance</td></tr><tr><td>Payout</td><td>Finance or payout provider</td></tr><tr><td>Reconciliation</td><td>Finance and Operations</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>The test coordinator should not perform every step alone. Each team should validate the stage it will own after launch.</p>","Prepare Sellers, Products and Customer Data":"<p>Prepare controlled data that represents the launch operating models and can be traced across every connected system.</p><h3>Representative test Sellers</h3><div class=\"detail-grid\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>TEST Seller A</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Commission model.</li><li>MConnect Product and Order flow.</li><li>Standard shipping.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>TEST Seller B</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Wholesale model.</li><li>Spreadsheet-managed Wholesale Price.</li><li>Seller Portal fulfilment.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>TEST Seller C</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Commission model.</li><li>Seller API connection.</li><li>Special shipping.</li></ul></article></div><div class=\"detail-grid detail-grid-two\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Products</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Simple and multi-Variant Products.</li><li>No-stock and Promotion-eligible Products.</li><li>Commission and wholesale Products.</li><li>Wholesale promotional-price Product where used.</li><li>Special-shipping Product.</li><li>Product from every planned ingestion method.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Customer data</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Approved test customer and controlled inbox.</li><li>Supported and unsupported delivery addresses.</li><li>Approved payment method.</li><li>Contact information suitable for notification testing.</li></ul></article></div><h3>Identifier register</h3><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Domain</th><th>Identifiers to retain</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Product</td><td>Source Product ID, Marketplacer Advert and Variant IDs, storefront Product and Variant IDs.</td></tr><tr><td>Transaction</td><td>Storefront Order ID, payment reference, Marketplacer Order ID, Seller Invoice and Line Item IDs.</td></tr><tr><td>Seller and fulfilment</td><td>Seller-platform Order ID, Shipment ID, Carrier and tracking reference.</td></tr><tr><td>Exceptions and Finance</td><td>Refund Request ID, Invoice Amendment, Remittance Advice ID and payout reference.</td></tr></tbody></table></div>","Record the Expected Commercial Outcome":"<p>Calculate the expected financial result before placing the Order. Do not use the Marketplacer result as the source for what the result was supposed to be.</p><div class=\"formula-grid\"><article class=\"formula-card\"><span class=\"formula-label\">Commission example</span><div class=\"formula-line\"><span>Customer item amount after discount</span><b>×</b><span>Approved commission rate</span></div><div class=\"formula-result\">$80.00 × 15% = $12.00 commission</div><p>Then apply approved postage commission, tax, Merchant Fees, Promotion funding and refund rules.</p></article><article class=\"formula-card\"><span class=\"formula-label\">Wholesale example</span><div class=\"formula-line\"><span>Customer retail item price</span><b>−</b><span>Seller Wholesale Price</span></div><div class=\"formula-result\">$100.00 − $30.00 = $70.00 indicative gross margin</div><p>Then apply tax, postage, Promotion funding, refund effects and other approved adjustments.</p></article></div><div class=\"detail-grid detail-grid-two\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Calculate separately</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Customer and Seller tax.</li><li>Postage and Merchant Fees.</li><li>Seller-funded and Operator-funded Promotions.</li><li>Refund and recovery effects.</li><li>Seller entitlement, Operator margin and payout amount.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Preserve historical values</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Retail and Sale prices.</li><li>Wholesale and promotional wholesale prices.</li><li>Commission rate and Package.</li><li>Promotion and funding allocation.</li><li>Tax, Merchant Fee and postage values.</li></ul></article></div><div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Use the values captured when the Order was created.</strong> Later Product, price or commercial changes must not alter the interpretation of a historical transaction.</div>","Test Customer Discovery and Product Selection":"<p>Confirm that the customer can find, understand and select the intended purchasable offer.</p><div class=\"detail-grid detail-grid-two\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Discovery and selection</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Navigation, search and filters return the intended Product.</li><li>The Product detail page shows the correct Seller, price, Sale or Promotion and shipping information.</li><li>Valid Variants can be selected and unavailable Variants are clear.</li><li>The correct Seller Variant is added to cart.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Golden Records, where used</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Shared Product content and the correct Golden Variant.</li><li>One or several Seller offers.</li><li>Partial Variant overlap and out-of-stock offers.</li><li>Correct offer selection or Buy Box result.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Protect confidential data</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Seller Wholesale Price is not shown.</li><li>Wholesale promotional price is not shown.</li><li>Operator margin is not shown.</li><li>Seller remittance or payout information is not shown.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Seller attribution</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Customer sees the intended Seller identity.</li><li>The selected offer belongs to the correct Seller.</li><li>The customer does not receive another Seller’s operational information.</li><li>Seller attribution remains correct in cart and checkout.</li></ul></article></div>","Test Price, Stock and Availability":"<p>Compare the same Variant across the complete customer path.</p><div class=\"reconciliation-flow\"><span>Seller source</span><b>→</b><span>Marketplacer Variant</span><b>→</b><span>Operator storefront</span><b>→</b><span>Cart</span><b>→</b><span>Checkout</span></div><div class=\"detail-grid\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Price</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Base retail price, Sale price and Promotion.</li><li>Tax, currency, regional pricing and rounding.</li><li>No unexpected price change between Product page, cart and checkout.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Stock</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Source quantity and stock buffer.</li><li>Marketplacer quantity and storefront availability.</li><li>Permitted Order quantity and post-Order quantity.</li><li>Zero-stock and replenishment behaviour.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Availability</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Publication and Product Vetting state.</li><li>Catalog Rule result and Seller online status.</li><li>Variant validity and regional eligibility.</li><li>Shipping eligibility and supported destination.</li></ul></article></div>","Test Cart and Shipping":"<p>Validate the cart as both a customer total and a Seller-level allocation.</p><div class=\"detail-grid detail-grid-two\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Single-Seller cart</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Correct Product, Variant, quantity and Seller.</li><li>Correct item price, Promotion, postage, tax and total.</li><li>One valid shipping option for the selected destination.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Multi-Seller cart</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Seller-specific Line Items and shipping.</li><li>Correct combined customer total.</li><li>Correct Promotion and tax allocation.</li><li>One Seller’s shipping failure does not corrupt another Seller’s calculation.</li></ul></article></div><h3>Shipping scenarios</h3><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Scenario group</th><th>Test coverage</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Destination</td><td>Supported postcode, unsupported postcode and Zone boundary.</td></tr><tr><td>Rates</td><td>Standard, express, free shipping and threshold boundaries.</td></tr><tr><td>Products</td><td>Different Shipping Profiles, bulky Products and Products with no applicable Rate.</td></tr><tr><td>Seller mix</td><td>Several Sellers, one unsupported Seller and Seller-specific shipping.</td></tr><tr><td>Conditional</td><td>Click and collect or international shipping where applicable.</td></tr></tbody></table></div><h3>Promotion and shipping</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>The Promotion applies to the intended item, shipping amount or both.</li><li>Only eligible Sellers and Products receive the adjustment.</li><li>The customer cannot complete checkout when no valid fulfilment path exists.</li></ul>","Test Checkout and Payment":"<p>Confirm that checkout preserves the approved customer data, delivery choice and financial total.</p><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Customer and address information are retained correctly.</li><li>The selected shipping option is retained.</li><li>The payment request equals the approved checkout total.</li><li>Payment is attempted once and the stable payment reference is retained.</li><li>The customer receives an accurate result.</li></ul><div class=\"detail-grid\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Payment succeeds</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Payment provider records success.</li><li>One marketplace Order is created.</li><li>Customer receives the correct confirmation.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Payment fails</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>No successful customer Order.</li><li>No fulfilment-ready Seller Invoice.</li><li>No Seller fulfilment request.</li><li>Customer receives a clear failure result.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Payment succeeds, downstream fails</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Search by External ID, payment reference and storefront Order reference.</li><li>Recover the original Order or reverse the payment.</li><li>Do not charge the customer or create the Order twice.</li></ul></article></div>","Test Marketplacer Order Creation":"<p>For connected marketplaces, <code class=\"code-pill\">orderCreate</code> is commonly used after payment to create the Marketplacer Order and the Seller-level Invoices required for fulfilment.</p><div class=\"detail-grid detail-grid-two\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Order integrity</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Exactly one Marketplacer Order.</li><li>Correct customer, address, Variant IDs and quantities.</li><li>Correct item, postage, tax and Promotion values.</li><li>Correct commercial-model data.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Traceability</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Storefront Order ID retained.</li><li>Payment reference retained.</li><li>Stable External IDs retained.</li><li>Operations can search by Marketplacer ID, storefront ID, customer or payment reference.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Seller delivery</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Correct Seller Invoice split.</li><li>The selected notification and integration method is tested.</li><li>Seller notifications are not assumed to occur unless the implementation requests or provides them.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Duplicate safety</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>An uncertain response is searched before retry.</li><li>The original Order is recovered where it already exists.</li><li>No duplicate Seller Invoice or Seller-system Order is created.</li></ul></article></div>","Test Multi-Seller Order Splitting":"<p>One Marketplacer Order represents the customer purchase. Each Seller Invoice represents one participating Seller’s portion.</p><div class=\"detail-grid detail-grid-two\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Customer Order</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Seller A Product 1.</li><li>Seller A Product 2.</li><li>Seller B Product 3.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Expected Seller split</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Seller A Invoice contains Products 1 and 2.</li><li>Seller B Invoice contains Product 3.</li><li>Each Invoice contains only the relevant quantities, shipping and commercial values.</li></ul></article></div><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>One customer Order is created.</li><li>The correct number of Seller Invoices is created.</li><li>Line Items, quantities, postage and Promotion allocation are correct per Seller.</li><li>Each Seller uses the correct commercial model.</li><li>No Seller sees another Seller’s operational or wholesale information.</li><li>The customer sees one coherent Order experience.</li></ul>","Test Seller Order Receipt":"<p>Test each planned Seller fulfilment method through the Seller’s normal Production-like workflow.</p><div class=\"detail-grid\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Seller Portal</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Seller Invoice appears once.</li><li>The correct Seller user can locate it.</li><li>Products, quantities and customer information are correct.</li><li>The Seller can progress the Order.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>MConnect</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Seller Invoice reaches the connected platform once.</li><li>Destination Order ID and expected tags are retained.</li><li>Financial values are represented correctly.</li><li>The Seller can fulfil through its normal workflow.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Seller API or middleware</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Invoice is retrieved or received through the approved event model.</li><li>Marketplacer identifiers are retained.</li><li>Seller-system Order is created once.</li><li>Errors, retries and acknowledgement are monitored.</li></ul></article></div><h3>Seller acknowledgement</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Order received.</li><li>Products and quantities understood.</li><li>Delivery expectation understood.</li><li>Customer and shipping information is sufficient.</li><li>Cancellation, return and escalation processes are understood.</li></ul>","Test Seller Fulfilment":"<p>Confirm that the Seller can dispatch the correct Line Items and return a complete Shipment record.</p><div class=\"detail-grid detail-grid-two\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Successful fulfilment</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Correct Line Items and quantities.</li><li>Dispatch date, Carrier and tracking code.</li><li>Marketplacer Shipment and Seller Invoice status.</li><li>Storefront and customer notification update.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Evidence</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Seller-platform fulfilment record.</li><li>Marketplacer Shipment ID.</li><li>Affected Line Items and dispatched quantities.</li><li>Carrier, tracking and customer communication.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Invalid attempts</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Missing or malformed tracking.</li><li>Invalid Carrier.</li><li>Quantity greater than ordered.</li><li>Cancelled quantity dispatched.</li><li>Duplicate fulfilment.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Source ownership</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>The authoritative fulfilment source is documented.</li><li>Manual and integrated fulfilment do not compete.</li><li>Failed fulfilment enters an owned recovery process.</li><li>Older updates do not overwrite newer status.</li></ul></article></div>","Test Partial and Split Fulfilment":"<div class=\"formula-grid\"><article class=\"formula-card\"><span class=\"formula-label\">Partial quantity</span><div class=\"formula-line\"><span>Ordered: 3</span><b>→</b><span>Dispatched: 2, outstanding: 1</span></div><div class=\"formula-result\">The remaining unit stays open</div><p>Customer status, Seller Invoice and remittance eligibility must reflect only the dispatched quantity.</p></article><article class=\"formula-card\"><span class=\"formula-label\">Split Shipment</span><div class=\"formula-line\"><span>Seller Invoice</span><b>→</b><span>Shipment 1 and Shipment 2</span></div><div class=\"formula-result\">Each parcel keeps its own tracking</div><p>The Seller Invoice must not appear complete before every required quantity is fulfilled or otherwise resolved.</p></article></div><div class=\"detail-grid detail-grid-two\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Partial fulfilment controls</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Only the dispatched quantity is marked fulfilled.</li><li>Outstanding quantity remains visible.</li><li>Seller can dispatch the remainder later.</li><li>Cancellation and return actions use the correct quantity.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Multi-Seller controls</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Seller A dispatch does not complete Seller B’s Invoice.</li><li>Tracking remains separate by parcel and Seller.</li><li>One Seller’s delay does not hide another Seller’s completed Shipment.</li><li>Customer Service can explain the separate outcomes.</li></ul></article></div>","Test Tracking and Customer Communications":"<p>Confirm that each communication is generated by the intended system, reaches the correct recipient and represents the current Order state.</p><div class=\"detail-grid detail-grid-two\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Communications to test</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Order confirmation.</li><li>Payment failure.</li><li>Shipment and partial Shipment.</li><li>Cancellation acknowledgement.</li><li>Return instructions.</li><li>Refund confirmation.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Validate every message</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Recipient and marketplace branding.</li><li>Order, Seller, Product and quantity references.</li><li>Carrier, tracking and Production links.</li><li>Support details and reply route.</li><li>No duplicate message or wholesale-data exposure.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Customer account</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Complete customer Order.</li><li>Seller-level or parcel-level status where designed.</li><li>Outstanding and fulfilled items.</li><li>Tracking, cancellations, returns and refunded amount.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Ownership</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Marketplacer-generated messages.</li><li>Storefront or Customer Service messages.</li><li>Seller-system notifications.</li><li>Payment and payout-provider notifications.</li></ul></article></div>","Test Commission-Model Orders":"<p>For a commission Seller, validate the complete commercial result using the values captured when the Order was created.</p><div class=\"detail-grid\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Standard Order</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Customer retail price, tax and postage.</li><li>Commission basis and rate.</li><li>Category, Brand or price-tier rule.</li><li>Commission on postage and Merchant Fee.</li><li>Seller entitlement, remittance and reporting.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Promotion Order</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Customer discount.</li><li>Seller-funded and Operator-funded portions.</li><li>Adjusted commission basis.</li><li>Tax and Merchant Fee treatment.</li><li>Seller entitlement and remittance impact.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Refunded Order</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Item and tax reversal.</li><li>Commission reversal under the approved rule.</li><li>Postage and Merchant Fee treatment.</li><li>Promotion-funding reversal.</li><li>Remittance Advice and credit-document adjustment.</li></ul></article></div><div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Use the historical Commission Package and Order values.</strong> Do not recalculate the transaction from the Seller’s current Product price or current Package.</div>","Test Wholesale-Model Orders":"<p>For a wholesale Seller, the Seller’s Wholesale Price determines item entitlement while the Operator controls or approves the customer-facing retail price.</p><div class=\"formula-grid\"><article class=\"formula-card\"><span class=\"formula-label\">Standard wholesale Order</span><div class=\"formula-line\"><span>Customer retail price: $100</span><b>−</b><span>Seller Wholesale Price: $30</span></div><div class=\"formula-result\">$70 indicative gross margin</div><p>Before tax, fees, Promotions, refunds and other approved adjustments.</p></article><article class=\"formula-card\"><span class=\"formula-label\">Protected retail price</span><div class=\"formula-line\"><span>Seller source price changes to $60</span><b>≠</b><span>Approved storefront price remains $100</span></div><div class=\"formula-result\">Source ownership remains intact</div><p>An unexpected overwrite must be detected and contained.</p></article></div><div class=\"detail-grid detail-grid-two\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Confirm the transaction</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Storefront shows the approved retail price.</li><li>Marketplacer retains the correct Wholesale Price.</li><li>Seller Invoice and remittance use the wholesale entitlement.</li><li>Finance can reconcile Operator margin.</li><li>No unintended commission is deducted.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Missing Wholesale Price</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Block or flag the Product.</li><li>Keep it outside the approved launch scope.</li><li>Do not use customer retail value as Seller entitlement.</li><li>Correct the authoritative source and retest.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Protect confidentiality</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Wholesale Price is not shown to customers.</li><li>Wholesale promotional price is not shown.</li><li>Operator margin is restricted to authorised users.</li><li>Seller RRP remains reference information unless explicitly used.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Refund and recovery</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Use the historical wholesale value.</li><li>Recover the correct Seller amount.</li><li>Adjust tax, postage and Promotion funding.</li><li>Correct remittance and Operator margin.</li></ul></article></div>","Test Mixed Commercial Models":"<p>A customer Order may contain commission and wholesale Sellers. Apply the correct model at the Seller Invoice or Line Item level rather than one Order-level formula.</p><div class=\"detail-grid detail-grid-two\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Seller A: commission</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Commission Package and applicable rule.</li><li>Merchant Fees and Promotion funding.</li><li>Commission-based Seller entitlement and refund reversal.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Seller B: wholesale</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Wholesale Price and Operator-controlled retail price.</li><li>Wholesale Seller entitlement and Operator margin.</li><li>No unintended commission and correct refund recovery.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Complete customer Order</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>One coherent checkout and customer total.</li><li>Correct shipping and Seller Invoice split.</li><li>Each Seller receives only its own information.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Finance reconciliation</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Each Seller is calculated using its assigned model.</li><li>Promotion funding is allocated correctly.</li><li>Refunding one Seller does not apply the other Seller’s model.</li></ul></article></div>","Test Sale Prices and Seller Discounts":"<p>A Seller Sale price and an Operator marketplace Promotion are different mechanisms and must be tested separately.</p><div class=\"detail-grid detail-grid-two\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Commission Seller Sale price</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Seller reduces the customer selling price.</li><li>Marketplacer and the storefront show the approved price.</li><li>Commission basis follows the approved rule.</li><li>Sale start, end and historical Order values are correct.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Wholesale Seller source price</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>A Seller source-price reduction does not automatically replace the Operator retail price.</li><li>The change is ignored, reviewed, transformed or applied through a separate Promotion according to the approved design.</li><li>Unexpected overwrites are monitored and contained.</li></ul></article></div><div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Example:</strong> A Seller source price falls by 40%, while the Operator intends a 20% customer discount. The integration must apply the approved marketplace rule rather than pass the full Seller reduction directly to the customer.</div>","Test Marketplace Promotions":"<p>Test each Promotion type, eligibility rule and commercial consequence planned for launch.</p><div class=\"detail-grid detail-grid-two\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Eligibility</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Eligible and ineligible Sellers.</li><li>Eligible and ineligible Categories or Products.</li><li>Minimum spend and customer requirements.</li><li>Start, end and overlapping Promotions.</li><li>Product already on Sale.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Customer result</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Correct Promotion displayed.</li><li>Correct discount in cart and checkout.</li><li>Ineligible Products unaffected.</li><li>Correct Marketplacer adjustment and Seller Invoice representation.</li><li>Correct refund reversal.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Operator governance</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Seller changes are not automatically passed to the storefront unless approved.</li><li>Integration logic decides whether to apply, transform, hold or reject a change.</li><li>Monitoring identifies unexpected Promotion or price effects.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Reporting and Finance</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Seller-funded and Operator-funded portions are visible.</li><li>Commission or wholesale calculations remain explainable.</li><li>Tax and Merchant Fee treatment are correct.</li><li>Refunds reverse the correct funding amounts.</li></ul></article></div>","Test Wholesale Promotional Prices":"<p>A wholesale promotional price changes the Seller’s temporary cost. It does not automatically change the customer-facing retail price.</p><div class=\"formula-grid\"><article class=\"formula-card\"><span class=\"formula-label\">Normal period</span><div class=\"formula-line\"><span>Retail: $100</span><b>−</b><span>Wholesale: $30</span></div><div class=\"formula-result\">$70 indicative gross margin</div></article><article class=\"formula-card\"><span class=\"formula-label\">Promotional period</span><div class=\"formula-line\"><span>Retail remains $100</span><b>−</b><span>Wholesale promotional price: $20</span></div><div class=\"formula-result\">$80 indicative gross margin</div></article></div><div class=\"detail-grid detail-grid-two\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Price controls</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Approved maintenance method.</li><li>Correct start and end dates.</li><li>Customer retail price remains protected.</li><li>Future Orders return to the normal Wholesale Price after expiry.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Integration controls</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Do not assume MConnect maintains the field.</li><li>The change is visible to the Operator.</li><li>Use the approved spreadsheet, API or other supported method.</li><li>Monitor unsupported or unexpected overwrites.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Transaction controls</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Eligible Seller Invoice uses the promotional wholesale value.</li><li>Historical Orders retain the applicable value.</li><li>Refunds use the historical Order value.</li><li>Finance can explain the temporary margin change.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Do not assume unavailable controls</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Do not design around an unreleased price-lock or approval feature.</li><li>Use source ownership, change control, monitoring and authorised processes that exist in the implementation.</li></ul></article></div>","Test Promotion Funding":"<p>Test customer discount and funding source as separate calculations.</p><div class=\"detail-grid\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Operator-funded</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Customer discount: $20.</li><li>Seller reduction: $0.</li><li>Operator funds: $20.</li><li>Seller entitlement remains protected.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Seller-funded</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Customer discount: $20.</li><li>Seller funds: $20.</li><li>Operator funds: $0.</li><li>Seller remittance reflects the withholding.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Split-funded</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Customer discount: $20.</li><li>Seller funds: $12.</li><li>Operator funds: $8.</li><li>Both amounts reverse correctly on refund.</li></ul></article></div><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Test commission and wholesale Sellers separately.</li><li>Test full and partial cancellation or refund.</li><li>Test multi-Seller allocation.</li><li>Confirm tax, commission or margin and remittance remain explainable.</li></ul>","Test Pre-Dispatch Cancellation":"<p>Pre-dispatch cancellation applies only before the affected quantity has been fulfilled.</p><div class=\"detail-grid detail-grid-two\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Seller-initiated cancellation</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Seller receives the Seller Invoice.</li><li>Seller identifies the unavailable Product or quantity.</li><li>The approved cancellation is created.</li><li>Operator review occurs where required.</li><li>Customer refund and communication are completed.</li><li>Seller financial adjustment and remittance are correct.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Operator-initiated cancellation</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Full Seller Invoice.</li><li>One Line Item or partial quantity.</li><li>One Seller in a multi-Seller Order.</li><li>One Seller cancels while another fulfils.</li><li>Duplicate cancellation is prevented.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Customer result</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Cancelled Product and quantity are clear.</li><li>Remaining Products stay active.</li><li>Refund amount is correct.</li><li>Fulfilment status and communication are updated.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Commercial result</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Commission, fees or wholesale entitlement reverse correctly.</li><li>Tax, postage and Promotion funding follow the approved rule.</li><li>Remittance excludes or recovers the cancelled amount.</li></ul></article></div>","Test Post-Dispatch Returns":"<p>Test the complete post-dispatch return journey.</p><div class=\"reconciliation-flow\"><span>Customer receives Product</span><b>→</b><span>Return requested</span><b>→</b><span>Refund Request created</span><b>→</b><span>Seller or Operator assessment</span><b>→</b><span>Return instructions</span><b>→</b><span>Product returned where required</span><b>→</b><span>Refund completed</span><b>→</b><span>Commercial and remittance adjustment</span></div><div class=\"detail-grid detail-grid-two\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Accepted return</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Correct Refund Reason and eligible window.</li><li>Correct Product, Variant and quantity.</li><li>Return-required or returnless decision.</li><li>Return instructions, address and tracking where used.</li><li>Approved customer refund and Seller adjustment.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Denied return</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Approved Deny Refund Reason.</li><li>Decision and evidence retained.</li><li>Customer communication is appropriate.</li><li>Payment is not refunded.</li><li>Seller remittance is not incorrectly reduced.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Multi-Seller isolation</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Seller A return does not alter Seller B’s fulfilment.</li><li>Seller B entitlement, remittance and payout remain unchanged.</li><li>Customer Service can explain the separate Seller outcomes.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Reconciliation</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Marketplacer workflow and payment-provider refund are both complete.</li><li>Invoice Amendment, Seller adjustment and remittance agree.</li><li>The customer is not refunded twice.</li></ul></article></div>","Test Partial and Full Refunds":"<div class=\"detail-grid\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Full refund</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Customer item value and tax.</li><li>Postage where approved.</li><li>Promotion and funding.</li><li>Commission or wholesale entitlement.</li><li>Merchant Fee and remittance treatment.</li><li>Accounting and payout recovery.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Partial quantity refund</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Example: ordered 3, refunded 1, retained 2.</li><li>Customer receives one-unit refund.</li><li>Remaining quantities stay fulfilled.</li><li>Seller adjustment and Promotion allocation cover one unit.</li><li>Remittance retains the correct amount for two units.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>One Line Item in a multi-Seller Order</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Only the affected Seller Invoice changes.</li><li>Customer Order total updates appropriately.</li><li>Other Seller fulfilment and remittance remain unchanged.</li><li>Payment refund matches the affected item.</li></ul></article></div><div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Refund after payout:</strong> Test the approved negative-balance, future-remittance offset or direct recovery process when the Seller has already been paid.</div>","Test Payment Refund Reconciliation":"<p>Marketplacer refund workflow and customer cash movement are separate control points. The scenario passes only when the marketplace record, customer refund and Seller financial adjustment agree.</p><div class=\"reconciliation-flow\"><span>Refund Request complete</span><b>+</b><span>Invoice Amendment complete</span><b>+</b><span>Payment-provider refund complete</span><b>+</b><span>Seller adjustment complete</span><b>=</b><span>Fully reconciled refund</span></div><div class=\"detail-grid\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Marketplacer complete, payment refund missing</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Generate an operational alert.</li><li>Prevent a duplicate refund.</li><li>Route the case to the payment owner.</li><li>Keep Customer Service informed.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Payment refund complete, Marketplacer missing</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Complete the Marketplacer workflow.</li><li>Create the correct Invoice Amendment.</li><li>Correct Seller remittance.</li><li>Retain the external refund reference.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Evidence</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Refund Request ID and approved amount.</li><li>Payment-provider refund ID and status.</li><li>Customer communication.</li><li>Invoice Amendment and Remittance Advice adjustment.</li></ul></article></div>","Test Remittance and Seller Payout":"<p>Before a Seller amount becomes payable, the Seller Invoice must satisfy the configured eligibility rules, including completion, approval and the applicable Remittance Delay. Marketplacer records the remittance workflow; the marketplace payout process or payout provider moves the funds.</p><h3>Remittance eligibility</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list\"><li>Completed Seller Invoice.</li><li>Configured Remittance Delay has passed.</li><li>No unresolved refund prevents release.</li><li>Authorised approval is complete.</li><li>The correct commercial model and historical Order values are used.</li></ul><div class=\"formula-grid\"><article class=\"formula-card\"><span class=\"formula-label\">Commission remittance</span><div class=\"formula-line\"><span>Seller sales entitlement</span><b>−</b><span>Commission, fees, Seller-funded adjustments and refunds</span></div><div class=\"formula-result\">Seller remittance</div><p>Include approved positive or negative adjustments and reconcile the Seller Remittance Advice.</p></article><article class=\"formula-card\"><span class=\"formula-label\">Wholesale remittance</span><div class=\"formula-line\"><span>Wholesale item entitlement and approved postage</span><b>−</b><span>Seller-funded adjustments and refunds</span></div><div class=\"formula-result\">Seller remittance</div><p>Do not use customer retail revenue as the wholesale Seller settlement basis.</p></article></div><h3>Actual payout</h3><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Control</th><th>Expected result</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Approval</td><td>An authorised user approves the exact Seller amount once.</td></tr><tr><td>Payment</td><td>The manual process or payout provider creates one traceable transaction.</td></tr><tr><td>Receipt</td><td>The Seller receives the correct amount in the approved account.</td></tr><tr><td>Failure handling</td><td>A failed payout is visible, owned and retried without duplication.</td></tr><tr><td>Reconciliation</td><td>The payout reference, Remittance Advice and Finance records agree.</td></tr></tbody></table></div>","Test Reporting and Operational Visibility":"<p>Confirm that the completed transaction and every exception can be located in the tools used after launch.</p><div class=\"detail-grid detail-grid-two\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Operator and marketplace reporting</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Dashboard, Orders and Seller Invoices.</li><li>Sales, Seller Performance and catalogue reporting.</li><li>Refunds, remittance, payout and Payment Events.</li><li>MConnect, Problem Reports, Activity Logs and External IDs.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>External reporting</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Payment-provider reports.</li><li>Seller platform or warehouse.</li><li>Customer Service platform.</li><li>Accounting system, data warehouse or analytics.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Required dimensions</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Order date, Seller, Product, Category and quantity.</li><li>Customer retail value and authorised wholesale value.</li><li>Commission, Merchant Fee, Promotion and funding.</li><li>Refund, remittance, Operator margin, Shipment and payout status.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Access controls</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Wholesale Price and Operator margin are restricted.</li><li>Customer data is visible only where operationally required.</li><li>Reports use consistent identifiers and time zones.</li><li>Finance can reconcile the same transaction across systems.</li></ul></article></div>","Test Customer Service Handoffs":"<p>Customer Service should be able to locate and explain the Order without depending on the integration team.</p><div class=\"detail-grid detail-grid-two\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Find and understand the Order</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Locate the customer Order and participating Sellers.</li><li>See Products, quantities, Shipment status and tracking.</li><li>Identify outstanding, cancelled, returned and refunded items.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Take the correct action</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Create or route a cancellation.</li><li>Create or route a return.</li><li>Determine whether the payment refund completed.</li><li>Explain the expected timeframe and escalate using stable IDs.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Explain a multi-Seller outcome</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>One Seller dispatched while another is outstanding.</li><li>One Seller cancelled or returned.</li><li>Separate tracking and refund amounts.</li><li>Separate Seller responsibilities.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Finance handoff</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Identify Marketplacer-complete but payment-incomplete refunds.</li><li>Identify payment-complete but marketplace-incomplete refunds.</li><li>Escalate remittance or payout recovery.</li><li>Do not interpret restricted Finance records without the Finance owner.</li></ul></article></div>","Test Failure and Recovery Scenarios":"<p>Test failures deliberately so the team proves detection, containment, recovery and reconciliation before launch.</p><div class=\"detail-grid detail-grid-two\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Product and catalogue</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Product unexpectedly removed.</li><li>Stale price or stock.</li><li>Invalid Product reaches the storefront.</li><li>Protected retail pricing is overwritten.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Payment and Order</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Payment fails.</li><li>Payment succeeds and <code class=\"code-pill\">orderCreate</code> returns an error.</li><li>Request times out or Marketplacer is temporarily unavailable.</li><li>Marketplacer Order exists while storefront reports failure.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Seller and fulfilment</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Seller Invoice is not delivered.</li><li>MConnect, Seller API or destination system is unavailable.</li><li>Destination Order already exists or is duplicated.</li><li>Shipment or tracking does not return.</li><li>Partial Shipment is interpreted as complete.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Refund and Finance</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Marketplacer refund completes but payment refund fails.</li><li>Payment refund completes but Marketplacer remains unchanged.</li><li>Refund is retried twice.</li><li>Seller remittance or payout has already been processed.</li></ul></article></div><h3>Every recovery must prove</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>The original record is identified.</li><li>Duplicate checks are complete.</li><li>The authoritative source is corrected through the approved repair method.</li><li>Customer and Seller outcomes are resolved.</li><li>Financial records are reconciled.</li><li>Root cause and affected records remain available for investigation.</li></ul>","Test Duplicate Prevention":"<p>Duplicate protection is required for customer Orders, Marketplacer Orders, Seller-system Orders, Shipments, refunds, remittances and payouts.</p><h3>Uncertain Order response</h3><div class=\"reconciliation-flow\"><span>Payment succeeds</span><b>→</b><span>orderCreate submitted</span><b>→</b><span>Response times out</span><b>→</b><span>Search by stable External ID and payment reference</span><b>→</b><span>Original Order found</span><b>→</b><span>Do not create a second Order</span></div><div class=\"detail-grid detail-grid-two\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Required controls</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Stable External ID and payment reference.</li><li>Unique processing record and controlled concurrency.</li><li>Query-before-retry.</li><li>Retry limits and reconciliation queue.</li><li>Manual recovery approval.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Webhook and event duplicates</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Store the event identifier or Idempotency Key.</li><li>Recognise repeated delivery.</li><li>Do not repeat the business action.</li><li>Return an appropriate acknowledgement when already processed.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Refund and payout duplicates</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Search for the original result after an uncertain response.</li><li>One Refund Request cannot move customer cash twice.</li><li>One Remittance Advice cannot create two payouts.</li><li>Manual payment requires independent review.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Seller-system duplicates</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Retain the Marketplacer source reference.</li><li>Recognise an existing destination Order.</li><li>Return the original destination identifier where appropriate.</li><li>Do not create a second fulfilment record.</li></ul></article></div>","Test Negative and Boundary Scenarios":"<p>Test values immediately below, at and above important boundaries, including permissions and integration limits.</p><div class=\"detail-grid detail-grid-two\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Quantity</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Zero and one.</li><li>Maximum permitted quantity.</li><li>Quantity greater than stock.</li><li>Minimum and maximum purchase quantity.</li><li>Partial quantity cancellation and refund.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Price and commercial data</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Zero or missing price where invalid.</li><li>Missing Wholesale Price.</li><li>Wholesale Price higher than customer retail price.</li><li>Sale price equal to or higher than retail price.</li><li>Promotion larger than eligible amount.</li><li>Rounding boundary.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Date and time</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Immediately before Promotion start.</li><li>Exact start and end time.</li><li>Immediately after expiry.</li><li>Wholesale promotional period.</li><li>Remittance Delay boundary.</li><li>Time-zone transition.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Shipping</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Postcode at Zone boundary.</li><li>Unsupported postcode.</li><li>Cart below, at and above free-shipping threshold.</li><li>No applicable Shipping Rate.</li><li>One unsupported Seller in a multi-Seller cart.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Users and permissions</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Unauthorised Seller cancellation.</li><li>Unauthorised Product approval.</li><li>Unauthorised payout approval.</li><li>Unauthorised wholesale-price access.</li><li>Unauthorised API key or Webhook change.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Integration boundaries</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Invalid or expired credential.</li><li>Wrong environment endpoint.</li><li>Out-of-order, delayed or duplicate event.</li><li>Unsupported field or payload.</li><li>Rate-limit or timeout response.</li></ul></article></div>","Capture End-to-End Evidence":"<p>The evidence bundle should allow another reviewer to reconstruct the complete transaction without repeating the test.</p><h3>Recommended evidence sequence</h3><div class=\"reconciliation-flow\"><span>Source Product</span><b>→</b><span>Marketplacer Product and Variant</span><b>→</b><span>Storefront Product</span><b>→</b><span>Cart and checkout</span><b>→</b><span>Payment result</span><b>→</b><span>Marketplacer Order</span><b>→</b><span>Seller Invoices</span><b>→</b><span>Seller-system Orders</span><b>→</b><span>Shipments and tracking</span><b>→</b><span>Refund where applicable</span><b>→</b><span>Remittance and payout</span><b>→</b><span>Reporting result</span></div><div class=\"detail-grid detail-grid-two\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Financial worksheet</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Customer retail amount.</li><li>Wholesale amount where applicable.</li><li>Commission and Merchant Fee.</li><li>Postage, tax and Promotion funding.</li><li>Refund, Seller remittance, Operator margin and payout.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Evidence record</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Test ID and environment.</li><li>Seller, Product and commercial model.</li><li>System identifiers and timestamps.</li><li>Expected and actual result.</li><li>Approver and linked defect where applicable.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Naming example</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>E2E-WHOLESALE-PROMO-004.</li><li>Environment: Sandbox or Production.</li><li>Seller: TEST Seller B.</li><li>Order: 10582.</li><li>Date and time zone.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Evidence quality</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Show the action and resulting business record.</li><li>Retain IDs, timestamps and financial values.</li><li>Do not rely on a generic success message.</li><li>Protect customer and Seller-sensitive information.</li></ul></article></div>","Record and Retest Defects":"<p>An end-to-end defect should identify the exact failing boundary and the complete business impact.</p><div class=\"detail-grid detail-grid-two\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Defect identity</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Test ID, environment and Seller.</li><li>Commercial model, Product and transaction identifiers.</li><li>Expected and actual result.</li><li>Last confirmed successful stage.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Impact and ownership</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Customer, Seller, financial, privacy and operational impact.</li><li>Severity and containment.</li><li>Owner, target resolution and recovery action.</li><li>Evidence and affected records.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Retest scope</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Original failed stage.</li><li>Complete transaction journey.</li><li>Related commercial model and multi-Seller scenario.</li><li>Negative, recovery, reporting and reconciliation scenarios.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Regression example</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>A wholesale-pricing fix must be retested across standard wholesale Orders, wholesale Promotions, refunds, remittance and storefront overwrite protection.</li></ul></article></div>","Define End-to-End Exit Criteria":"<p>End-to-end testing is complete only when the approved journeys, financial outcomes, recovery controls and cross-functional approvals have passed.</p><div class=\"detail-grid detail-grid-two\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Transactions and fulfilment</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Single-Seller and multi-Seller Orders.</li><li>Commission, wholesale and mixed models where applicable.</li><li>Seller Invoice receipt.</li><li>Full, partial and split fulfilment.</li><li>Tracking and customer communications.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Commercials and exceptions</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Sale prices and Promotions.</li><li>Promotion funding and wholesale promotional prices.</li><li>Cancellations, returns, denials and refunds.</li><li>Payment-refund reconciliation.</li><li>Remittance and payout.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Operations and recovery</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Reporting and Customer Service handoffs.</li><li>Failure recovery and duplicate prevention.</li><li>Negative and boundary scenarios.</li><li>Evidence and defect retesting.</li><li>Cross-functional approval.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Launch blockers closed</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>No unrecoverable payment or duplicate transaction.</li><li>No incorrect customer price or Seller entitlement.</li><li>No wrong Seller Invoice or data exposure.</li><li>No unresolved refund, remittance or payout mismatch.</li><li>Monitoring and duplicate-safe recovery are available.</li></ul></article></div><div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Next step:</strong> Continue to <a href=\"?page=seller-launch-readiness\">Seller Launch Readiness</a>.</div><h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"link-list\"><li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/operator-api/examples/orders/howto_order/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Creating Orders</a></li><li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/operator-api/examples/orders/howto_wholesale_order/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Wholesale Orders</a></li><li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/seller-api/examples/shipping/creating_shipments/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Creating Shipments</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/8837682695053-Search-and-find-orders-in-the-Seller-Portal\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Search and find Orders in the Seller Portal</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/8838299197197-Dispatch-orders-from-the-Seller-Portal\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Dispatch Orders from the Seller Portal</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360040011851-Enable-and-use-the-returns-module\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Enable and use the returns module</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360052908272-Seller-payments-and-remittance-workflow\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Seller payments and remittance workflow</a></li><li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/webhooks/webhookretries/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Webhook Retry Policy</a></li><li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/webhooks/deduplication/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Webhook Deduplication</a></li></ul>","Operator End-to-End Checklist":"<p>Before approving End-to-End Testing, confirm that:</p><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Entry criteria were met.</li><li>One test coordinator owned execution.</li><li>Every journey had a named owner.</li><li>Sellers represented each launch commercial model and fulfilment method.</li><li>Products represented each launch ingestion method.</li><li>Commission and wholesale scenarios were tested separately.</li><li>Customer retail and Seller wholesale pricing remained separated.</li><li>Seller source pricing did not overwrite Operator-controlled retail pricing.</li><li>Wholesale promotional pricing was tested where applicable.</li><li>Customer discovery, Variant selection, price, stock and availability passed.</li><li>Single-Seller and multi-Seller cart and shipping passed.</li><li>Checkout, payment success, payment failure and uncertain outcomes passed.</li><li>One Marketplacer Order was created per customer transaction.</li><li>Stable External IDs and payment references were retained.</li><li>Seller Invoice splitting and Seller receipt passed.</li><li>Every launch fulfilment method passed.</li><li>Full, partial and split fulfilment passed.</li><li>Tracking reached the customer.</li><li>Customer communications passed.</li><li>Commission, wholesale and mixed-model calculations passed where applicable.</li><li>Sale-price behaviour and Promotion funding passed.</li><li>Wholesale promotional prices did not automatically change customer prices.</li><li>Pre-dispatch cancellation and post-dispatch return passed.</li><li>Denial, partial refund and full refund passed.</li><li>Payment-provider refunds reconciled with Marketplacer records.</li><li>Seller remittance and payout controls passed.</li><li>Reporting and Customer Service handoffs passed.</li><li>Timeout recovery and duplicate prevention passed.</li><li>Negative and boundary scenarios passed.</li><li>Evidence covered the complete transaction.</li><li>Failed tests and regression scope were retested.</li><li>No launch-blocking defect remains.</li><li>Cross-functional approval was recorded.</li></ul>"},"related":[["testing-strategy","Testing Strategy"],["configuration-testing","Marketplace Configuration Testing"],["catalogue-testing","Catalogue Testing"],["seller-launch-readiness","Seller Launch Readiness"],["production-readiness","Production Readiness"],["go-live","Go-Live"],["order-architecture","Order Architecture"],["refund-foundations","Refund Foundations"],["remittances","Remittances"],["integration-troubleshooting","Integration Troubleshooting"]]},"seller-launch-readiness":{"summary":"Confirm that each launch Seller has completed the required commercial, account, integration, catalogue, operational, financial and support preparations, demonstrated its ability to trade through the approved Production workflow, and received formal approval before customer Orders are enabled.","audience":["Seller management","Marketplace operations","Catalogue","Ecommerce","Technology and integrations","Finance","Customer service","Commercial","Legal","Security","Participating Sellers"],"sections":{"Understand Seller Launch Readiness":"<p>Seller Launch Readiness is the final evidence-based review of one Seller. It confirms that commercial, account, connection, catalogue, operational, financial, training and support work has passed before customer Orders are enabled.</p><div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Seller onboarding</strong><span>Agreement, information, account and connection</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Readiness evidence</strong><span>Catalogue, transaction and Finance results</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Risk review</strong><span>Exceptions, controls and owners</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Approval</strong><span>Cross-functional Seller decision</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Activation</strong><span>Approved scope only</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Early life</strong><span>Monitoring and containment</span></div></div><div class=\"callout note\"><strong>This is an approval gate, not another onboarding guide.</strong> Use Seller Lifecycle, Seller Information, Account Creation, Default Seller Configuration, Seller Portal, Seller Onboarding Process and Support Boundaries for the detailed work.</div>","Position the Gate in the Seller Lifecycle":"<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Recruit and qualify</strong><span>Seller proposition and fit</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Agree terms</strong><span>Commercial and operating model</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Create and connect</strong><span>Production account, users and integration</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Approve catalogue</strong><span>Products, Mapping, rules and vetting</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Prove operations</strong><span>Order, fulfilment, exceptions and Finance</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Seller Launch Readiness</strong><span>Approve or defer the Seller</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Active management</strong><span>Early-life monitoring and Seller Performance</span></div></div><p>Seller approval is an input into Production Readiness. It does not approve the marketplace or execute Go-Live.</p>","Define the Seller Launch Scope":"<ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Legal and trading name, Production Seller ID and target activation date.</li><li>Commercial model, approved Categories, Brands, Products and Variants.</li><li>Excluded, deferred and restricted Products.</li><li>Regions, shipping methods, fulfilment and return model.</li><li>Product-ingestion and Seller Invoice-delivery method.</li><li>Payout model and launch-volume assumptions.</li></ul><p>Reconcile the commercially approved assortment to Products supplied, imported, mapped, vetted and intended for publication.</p>","Establish Seller Readiness Entry Criteria":"<h3>Before you begin</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list\"><li>Commercial terms and legal information are approved.</li><li>Production Seller account, users and Seller-specific settings exist.</li><li>Product connection and representative catalogue are available.</li><li>Catalogue Testing evidence exists for the launch assortment.</li><li>The Seller can receive and fulfil a Seller Invoice.</li><li>Finance has validated the commercial model and payout ownership.</li><li>Seller training, contacts and escalation routes are available.</li></ul><div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Do not turn a fundamental prerequisite into a conditional approval.</strong> Unsigned terms, missing Wholesale Prices, no shipping, no Order receipt, no fulfilment or unresolved privacy risk are blockers.</div>","Maintain the Seller Readiness Register":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Domain</th><th>Evidence</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Scope</td><td>Approved Categories, Products, Variants and exclusions</td></tr><tr><td>Commercial</td><td>Agreement and commission, wholesale or hybrid model</td></tr><tr><td>Account and access</td><td>Seller ID, settings, users, MFA or SSO</td></tr><tr><td>Connection</td><td>Production credentials, ownership, monitoring and recovery</td></tr><tr><td>Catalogue</td><td>Counts, Mapping, Catalog Rules, Product Vetting and publication</td></tr><tr><td>Operations</td><td>Order receipt, fulfilment, tracking, cancellation and returns</td></tr><tr><td>Finance</td><td>Calculation, remittance, payout and verification</td></tr><tr><td>Competency and support</td><td>Seller demonstration, contacts and handover</td></tr><tr><td>Risk and approval</td><td>Open issues, controls, stop conditions and approvers</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Use explicit Not Started, In Progress, Blocked, Ready for Review, Passed, Conditionally Passed, Not Applicable, Failed and Deferred statuses. Separate activity completion from readiness outcome.</p>","Confirm Commercial, Legal and Policy Approval":"<ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Signed agreement and correct legal entity.</li><li>Commission, wholesale or approved hybrid model.</li><li>Customer retail-pricing authority and Seller RRP treatment.</li><li>Wholesale Price and wholesale promotional-price responsibilities.</li><li>Commission on postage, Merchant Fees, tax and Promotion funding.</li><li>Fulfilment, cancellation, return, refund and customer-data responsibilities.</li><li>Remittance Delay, payout method, chargeback and post-payout recovery.</li><li>Product, Category, regulatory and policy restrictions.</li></ul><p>Translate every material term into a Marketplacer setting, Product field, integration rule, operational process and test case. The configured result must match the agreement.</p>","Confirm Production Account and Access Readiness":"<ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Correct Production Seller ID, legal and trading information, region and currency.</li><li>Correct commercial model, Commission Package, wholesale setting and Seller overrides.</li><li>Product Vetting, Order, Product, API, MConnect, cancellation, refund and shipping permissions.</li><li>Named primary, backup, Catalogue, fulfilment, Finance and technical users.</li><li>MFA or SSO, recovery, least privilege and removal of test or former users.</li><li>Production credentials stored securely and revocable.</li></ul><p>This gate passes when the Seller can log in, perform its responsibilities, cannot access restricted functions and the account reflects the approved agreement.</p>","Confirm Connection and Data Ownership Readiness":"<p>Record whether the Seller uses Seller Portal, Bulk Product Management, MConnect, Seller API, feed, middleware or an Operator-managed process.</p><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Production credentials and endpoints.</li><li>Product creation and updates, stock, Seller Invoice delivery and fulfilment return.</li><li>Visible errors, alerts, named owners and manual recovery.</li><li>Duplicate-safe retries and environment separation.</li><li>Source-of-truth register for Product content, Category, Brand, retail, Wholesale Price, stock, shipping, fulfilment and exceptions.</li><li>Wholesale pricing and protected Operator retail fields are not overwritten.</li></ul><p>Use Seller Onboarding Support Boundaries to confirm what the Seller, Operator, partner, payment provider and Marketplacer Support own.</p>","Confirm Assortment and Catalogue Approval":"<ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Approved Product and Variant counts reconcile to imported, mapped, vetted, online and storefront counts.</li><li>Representative Product data, images, attributes, tax and shipping pass.</li><li>Mapping is complete for the launch assortment.</li><li>Catalog Rules pass and the Seller can correct the authoritative source.</li><li>Product Vetting passes and rejected Products remain offline.</li><li>Commission and wholesale Product data are correct.</li><li>Deferred and restricted Products remain unavailable.</li></ul><p>Use Catalogue Testing evidence rather than repeating the full ingestion, Mapping or vetting procedures.</p>","Confirm Pricing, Stock, Shipping and Tax Readiness":"<h3>Pricing</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Customer retail, Sale, Wholesale Price and wholesale promotional price are correct.</li><li>Seller RRP does not determine wholesale settlement.</li><li>Seller source pricing cannot overwrite protected retail pricing.</li></ul><h3>Stock</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Source, update frequency, buffer, zero-stock, replenishment, source removal and outage process are understood.</li></ul><h3>Shipping and tax</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Shipping Profiles, Zones, Rates, Carriers, return address, dispatch SLA and special fulfilment pass.</li><li>Seller tax status, marketplace tax model and transaction tax output pass.</li></ul>","Confirm Order, Fulfilment and Exception Readiness":"<ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Seller receives one Seller Invoice through its actual launch method.</li><li>Correct Products, Variants, quantities, customer and shipping data appear.</li><li>Destination-system Order identity and duplicate prevention pass.</li><li>Seller completes full fulfilment and valid tracking.</li><li>Partial or split fulfilment is tested or demonstrated where applicable.</li><li>Seller understands pre-dispatch cancellation, post-dispatch return, payment-refund ownership and remittance effect.</li><li>Seller does not issue uncoordinated off-platform refunds.</li></ul><p>The Seller should perform its own operational actions rather than the Operator completing every step on its behalf.</p>","Confirm Finance, Remittance and Payout Readiness":"<ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Finance reproduces the commission or wholesale calculation independently.</li><li>Merchant Fees, tax, Promotion funding, refunds and Seller entitlement are correct.</li><li>Remittance Delay, schedule, eligibility and Advice recipient are correct.</li><li>Manual or automated payout, approver, account, currency and failure process are complete.</li><li>Duplicate payout and negative-balance controls are understood.</li><li>KYC or AML and payout verification are complete where required.</li></ul><div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Trading before payout readiness requires a formal exception.</strong> Record Finance, Legal or Compliance approval, funds-holding plan, exposure limit, completion date and stop condition.</div>","Confirm Seller Competency and Support Handover":"<ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Seller demonstrates its actual Product, stock, Order, fulfilment, tracking, return and remittance workflow.</li><li>Seller can identify an integration error and follow the recovery or escalation route.</li><li>Primary and backup operational contacts are available.</li><li>Catalogue, fulfilment, Customer Service, Finance, technical and emergency responsibilities are assigned.</li><li>Seller resources and marketplace policies are provided.</li><li>Operator, partner, payment, payout and Marketplacer Support boundaries are understood.</li><li>Business-as-usual owner accepts the handover.</li></ul><div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Attendance is not competency.</strong> The Seller should demonstrate the tasks it will perform after launch.</div>","Complete Controlled Seller Launch Validation":"<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Approved Production Product</strong><span>Correct Product, Variant, retail, wholesale, stock and shipping</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Controlled checkout</strong><span>Payment succeeds once</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Marketplacer</strong><span>One Order and correct Seller Invoice</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Seller</strong><span>Receipt, fulfilment and tracking</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Customer</strong><span>Correct status and communication</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Finance</strong><span>Commercial and remittance outcome</span></div></div><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Capture Seller, Product, payment, Order, Seller Invoice, destination Order, Shipment and Finance identifiers.</li><li>Use the Seller’s own operational users and systems.</li><li>Demonstrate one applicable exception in Production or Sandbox where safer.</li><li>Confirm the Seller can find and explain the transaction afterward.</li></ul>","Review Risks and Decide Seller Approval":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Decision</th><th>Use</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Approved for Launch</td><td>All required controls pass.</td></tr><tr><td>Conditionally Approved</td><td>Limited isolated issue with tested control, owner, date, monitoring and stop condition.</td></tr><tr><td>Deferred</td><td>Seller remains safely outside the launch scope.</td></tr><tr><td>Blocked</td><td>A prerequisite or launch-blocking failure remains.</td></tr><tr><td>Removed from Scope</td><td>Seller will not launch under the current plan.</td></tr></tbody></table></div><h3>Do not conditionally approve</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Incorrect retail pricing or missing Wholesale Price.</li><li>Unreliable stock or no valid shipping.</li><li>Untested Seller Invoice receipt or fulfilment.</li><li>Duplicate Order risk or customer-data exposure.</li><li>Incorrect commission, Seller entitlement, refund, remittance or payout.</li><li>Unsafe credentials or no operational Seller contact.</li></ul>","Activate and Monitor the Seller":"<ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Activate only the approved Seller and Product scope.</li><li>Keep deferred Products, regions and Promotions offline.</li><li>Monitor Product visibility, pricing, Wholesale Price, stock, shipping and integration health.</li><li>Monitor Seller Invoice receipt, fulfilment, tracking, cancellations, returns and refunds.</li><li>Review first remittance and payout cycle.</li><li>Use direct Order monitoring until enough history exists for Seller Performance trends.</li></ul><p>Expand assortment, regions or volume only after the current scope is stable. Treat material expansion as a controlled mini-onboarding.</p>","Pause, Recover or Defer the Seller":"<p>Use the smallest effective containment action when continued trade creates unacceptable customer, Seller, financial, privacy or security risk.</p><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Take affected Products offline or pause the Seller’s storefront availability.</li><li>Pause Product or Seller Invoice sync, API worker or Webhook.</li><li>Remove Promotion eligibility.</li><li>Hold remittance or payout.</li><li>Restrict compromised access or high-risk Categories.</li><li>Preserve access needed to fulfil open Orders, process returns and reconcile Finance.</li></ul><p>Resume only after root cause, authoritative-source correction, affected-record reconciliation, fix testing, regression, monitoring and authorised approval.</p>","Operator Seller Launch Readiness Checklist":"<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Seller scope, owner, target date, evidence and approval authority are recorded.</li><li>Agreement, commercial model, legal information and policies are approved.</li><li>Production account, users, security and Seller overrides are correct.</li><li>Connection, source ownership, monitoring and duplicate-safe recovery pass.</li><li>Assortment, Mapping, Catalog Rules, Product Vetting and publication pass.</li><li>Retail, wholesale, stock, shipping and tax pass.</li><li>Seller Invoice receipt, fulfilment, tracking and one exception pass.</li><li>Commission or wholesale calculation, remittance, payout and verification pass.</li><li>Seller demonstrates competency and accepts support handover.</li><li>Controlled Production validation passes.</li><li>Open risks, stop conditions, monitoring and approval are recorded.</li></ul><h3>This page is complete when</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list\"><li>The Seller has passed every applicable readiness domain.</li><li>Conditional items are isolated and formally approved.</li><li>The approved activation scope matches the evidence.</li><li>Early-life monitoring and containment are ready.</li></ul><div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Next step:</strong> Continue to <a href=\"?page=production-readiness\">Production Readiness</a>.</div><h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"link-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/4404678147853-Information-to-collect-from-sellers-for-onboarding\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Information to collect from Sellers</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/31441867032717-Manage-Sellers-Page\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Manage Sellers</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/25930591592973-Seller-settings\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Seller Settings</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/32217510943245-Create-seller-onboarding-processes\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Create Seller onboarding processes</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/39816929271693-Manage-Multi-Factor-Authentication-in-the-Seller-Portal\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Manage Seller MFA</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/8837682695053-Search-and-find-orders-in-the-Seller-Portal\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Search and find Orders in the Seller Portal</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/8838299197197-Dispatch-orders-from-the-Seller-Portal\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Dispatch Orders from the Seller Portal</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/8838370021773-Cancel-an-order-as-a-seller\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Cancel an Order as a Seller</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360040011851-Enable-and-use-the-returns-module\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Enable and use the returns module</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/41580276790669-Business-verification-for-payouts-KYC-AML-for-Sellers\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Business verification for payouts</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/25570670327437-Configure-Seller-Performance-SLAs\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Configure Seller Performance SLAs</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/25599850695821-Intro-to-the-Seller-Performance-dashboard\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Seller Performance dashboard</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["seller-lifecycle","Seller Lifecycle"],["seller-information","Seller Information to Collect"],["seller-account-creation","Seller Account Creation"],["default-seller-configuration","Default Seller Configuration"],["seller-portal","Seller Portal"],["seller-onboarding-process","Seller Onboarding Process"],["seller-support-boundaries","Seller Onboarding Support Boundaries"],["seller-performance","Seller Performance"],["catalogue-testing","Catalogue Testing"],["end-to-end-testing","End-to-End Testing"],["production-readiness","Production Readiness"],["go-live","Go-Live"]]},"production-readiness":{"summary":"Confirm that the approved launch scope exists correctly in Production and that Sellers, Products, customer journeys, integrations, Finance operations, monitoring, support teams and containment controls are ready before real customer trading begins.","audience":["Marketplace leadership","Marketplace operations","Ecommerce","Product","Technology and integrations","Catalogue","Finance","Customer service","Seller management","Security","Commercial","Implementation partners"],"sections":{"Understand Production Readiness":"<p>Production Readiness is the final marketplace-wide assurance and Go or No-Go gate. It confirms that the approved result exists in Production and that the marketplace can trade safely.</p><div class=\"readiness-equation\"><article><span class=\"equation-kicker\">Tested</span><strong>Configuration and catalogue</strong><p>Approved settings, Product data and customer presentation.</p></article><span class=\"equation-symbol\">+</span><article><span class=\"equation-kicker\">Approved</span><strong>Sellers and operations</strong><p>Seller readiness, fulfilment, support and incident ownership.</p></article><span class=\"equation-symbol\">+</span><article><span class=\"equation-kicker\">Reconciled</span><strong>Integrations and Finance</strong><p>Payments, Orders, refunds, remittance, payout and monitoring.</p></article><span class=\"equation-symbol\">=</span><article class=\"equation-result\"><span class=\"equation-kicker\">Decision</span><strong>Production readiness</strong><p>Go, Conditional Go or No-Go.</p></article></div><div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Before you begin:</strong> Complete the agreed Configuration, Catalogue and End-to-End Testing scope, approve each launch Seller, close launch-blocking defects and make the evidence available to the Production Readiness approvers.</div>","Distinguish Production Readiness from Testing and Go-Live":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Stage</th><th>Primary question</th><th>Output</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Testing</td><td>Did the agreed scenarios pass in the appropriate environment?</td><td>Approved evidence and closed or controlled defects</td></tr><tr><td>Seller Launch Readiness</td><td>Can each approved Seller trade safely?</td><td>Seller-specific launch approval</td></tr><tr><td>Production Readiness</td><td>Does the complete approved result exist in Production?</td><td>Go, Conditional Go or No-Go</td></tr><tr><td>Go-Live</td><td>Can the approved scope be activated, monitored and controlled?</td><td>Controlled launch and hypercare</td></tr></tbody></table></div><div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Keep approval and execution separate.</strong> Production Readiness ends when formal approval is recorded. Go-Live begins by executing that approved scope.</div>","Establish the Production Readiness Register":"<p>Maintain one marketplace-wide register. Reference evidence from the detailed testing pages instead of repeating every test inside the readiness meeting.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>What to record</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Readiness item</td><td>The Production requirement or launch dependency</td></tr><tr><td>Owner</td><td>The person accountable for completion</td></tr><tr><td>Evidence</td><td>Production record, test result, calculation, dashboard or runbook</td></tr><tr><td>Status</td><td>Not started, in progress, blocked, conditionally ready or passed</td></tr><tr><td>Risk and control</td><td>Customer, Seller, financial or operational exposure and the containment</td></tr><tr><td>Approver</td><td>The authorised person accepting completion or residual risk</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Use one stable readiness ID for each item so it can be referenced in defects, launch decisions and the runbook.</p>","Confirm Launch Scope and Freeze the Baseline":"<div class=\"detail-grid\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Launch scope</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Approved Sellers, Categories, Products, Variants and regions.</li><li>Commercial models, payment methods, shipping methods and Promotions.</li><li>Production integrations and customer channels.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Timing and coverage</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Launch date, time and time zone.</li><li>Expected traffic and transaction volume.</li><li>Launch-day operational, technical, Finance and support coverage.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Deferred scope and risk</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Deferred Sellers, Products, regions and capabilities.</li><li>Accepted risks, owners, monitoring and stop conditions.</li><li>Items that must remain unavailable at launch.</li></ul></article></div><div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Freeze high-risk changes before approval.</strong> An emergency change requires a recorded reason, authorised approval, targeted retesting, regression and updated evidence.</div>","Verify the Production Environment and Access":"<div class=\"detail-grid\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Production endpoints</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Operator Portal, Seller Portal and storefront URLs.</li><li>Payment, payout, API, Webhook and MConnect endpoints.</li><li>Email routing, callbacks and monitoring destinations.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Environment separation</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>No Sandbox endpoint, test credential or staging callback remains.</li><li>Intentional Sandbox and Production differences are documented.</li><li>Production is checked directly rather than inferred from Sandbox.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Access and security</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Production users, roles, MFA, SSO and emergency access are ready.</li><li>Temporary implementation access is reviewed.</li><li>Obsolete credentials and users are removed or disabled.</li></ul></article></div><div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Production is the source of truth.</strong> A passing Sandbox result does not prove that the same setting, connection, Seller or Product exists in Production.</div>","Confirm the Customer Experience and Communications":"<div class=\"detail-grid detail-grid-two\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Discover</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Homepage and navigation.</li><li>Categories, search and filters.</li><li>Product page, Variant selection, Seller attribution and availability.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Buy</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Retail price, Sale price and Promotion.</li><li>Stock, shipping, tax and multi-Seller totals.</li><li>Cart, checkout, payment and Order confirmation.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Communicate</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>Order and Shipment updates.</li><li>Cancellation, return and refund communications.</li><li>Seller Invoice, remittance and operational notifications.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Protect the experience</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Correct branding, Production links, recipients and reply routes.</li><li>No duplicate communication.</li><li>No wholesale or internal financial data exposed to customers.</li></ul></article></div>","Confirm Seller and Catalogue Readiness":"<p>Every launch Seller must have passed Seller Launch Readiness. Reconcile the approved catalogue from source scope to customer visibility.</p><div class=\"reconciliation-flow\"><span>Approved launch scope</span><b>→</b><span>Imported</span><b>→</b><span>Mapped</span><b>→</b><span>Vetted</span><b>→</b><span>Online</span><b>→</b><span>Visible in storefront</span></div><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Readiness area</th><th>Production confirmation</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Seller</td><td>Connection, Order receipt, fulfilment, support contact and approved commercial model</td></tr><tr><td>Catalogue</td><td>Product and Variant counts reconcile; Mapping, Catalog Rules and Product Vetting are complete</td></tr><tr><td>Commercial data</td><td>Retail and Wholesale Prices, Sale values and promotional wholesale values are correct</td></tr><tr><td>Operational data</td><td>Stock, shipping and tax are valid for every purchasable Variant</td></tr><tr><td>Excluded scope</td><td>Deferred, restricted, invalid and unmapped Products remain unavailable</td></tr></tbody></table></div>","Confirm Commercial and Finance Readiness":"<div class=\"formula-grid\"><article class=\"formula-card\"><span class=\"formula-label\">Commission model</span><div class=\"formula-line\"><span>Customer selling amount</span><b>−</b><span>Commission and applicable Seller adjustments</span></div><div class=\"formula-result\">Seller entitlement</div><p>Confirm the assigned Commission Package, rule priority, postage, Promotion funding, tax, fees and refund treatment.</p></article><article class=\"formula-card\"><span class=\"formula-label\">Wholesale model</span><div class=\"formula-line\"><span>Operator retail revenue</span><b>−</b><span>Seller wholesale entitlement</span></div><div class=\"formula-result\">Indicative Operator gross margin</div><p>Confirm Wholesale Prices are complete, retail pricing is protected, Seller RRP is reference information and no unintended commission applies.</p></article></div><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Finance control</th><th>Production readiness evidence</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Payment and Order</td><td>One customer payment reconciles to one recoverable Marketplacer Order</td></tr><tr><td>Tax and fees</td><td>Item, postage, commission, Merchant Fee, withholding, currency and rounding are approved</td></tr><tr><td>Refunds</td><td>Marketplacer workflow, Invoice Amendment and payment-provider refund can be reconciled</td></tr><tr><td>Remittance</td><td>Delay, schedule, eligibility, approval and negative-balance treatment are understood</td></tr><tr><td>Payout</td><td>Manual payout or MPay, verification, failure handling and reconciliation have named owners</td></tr><tr><td>First financial cycle</td><td>Finance and accounting owners are available to review the first live cycle</td></tr></tbody></table></div>","Confirm Integrations, Monitoring and Reconciliation":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Boundary</th><th>Production proof</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Seller source → Marketplacer</td><td>Product, price and stock reach the correct Product and Variant</td></tr><tr><td>Marketplacer → storefront</td><td>Approved Product data and availability reach the customer experience</td></tr><tr><td>Storefront → payment</td><td>The approved amount and stable payment reference are retained</td></tr><tr><td>Storefront → Marketplacer Order</td><td>One recoverable Order is created with stable External IDs</td></tr><tr><td>Marketplacer → Seller system</td><td>The correct Seller Invoice reaches the correct Seller once</td></tr><tr><td>Seller fulfilment → Marketplacer</td><td>Shipment, Carrier and tracking return correctly</td></tr><tr><td>Refund workflow → payment provider</td><td>Marketplace records and customer cash movement reconcile</td></tr><tr><td>Remittance → payout provider</td><td>One approved Seller amount results in one traceable payout</td></tr></tbody></table></div><div class=\"detail-grid detail-grid-two\"><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Monitor</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list compact-list\"><li>API errors and uncertain outcomes.</li><li>Webhook Sent, Rejected, Failed and Skipped states.</li><li>MConnect Product, Seller Invoice and fulfilment health.</li><li>Queue backlog, delayed events and duplicate attempts.</li></ul></article><article class=\"detail-panel\"><h3>Own and recover</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list compact-list\"><li>Stable External IDs and reconciliation queries.</li><li>Duplicate-safe retries and manual recovery approval.</li><li>Named dashboard, alert, exception-queue and first-response owners.</li><li>Recent relevant Developer and Changelog updates reviewed.</li></ul></article></div>","Confirm Support and Incident Readiness":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Team</th><th>Must be ready to</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Customer Service</td><td>Find and explain multi-Seller Orders, Shipments, cancellations, returns and refunds</td></tr><tr><td>Seller Support</td><td>Manage Product, Mapping, vetting, Seller Invoice and fulfilment issues</td></tr><tr><td>Finance</td><td>Investigate payment, refund, remittance and payout differences</td></tr><tr><td>Technology and integrations</td><td>Identify failing boundaries, contain impact and recover safely</td></tr><tr><td>Marketplace leadership</td><td>Make Go, pause, scope-reduction and emergency-change decisions</td></tr><tr><td>Marketplacer Support liaison</td><td>Submit an evidence-backed request and coordinate updates</td></tr></tbody></table></div><div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Detect</strong><span>Confirm impact and evidence</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Assess</strong><span>Set severity, owner and decision time</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Contain</strong><span>Use the smallest effective control</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Recover</strong><span>Correct the authoritative source</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Reconcile</strong><span>Identify every affected record</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Communicate</strong><span>Update customers, Sellers and teams</span></div></div>","Prepare the Production Smoke Test and Containment Controls":"<h3>Controlled Production smoke test</h3><div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Approved Product</strong><span>Correct retail price, stock, shipping and tax</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Checkout and payment</strong><span>One approved live transaction</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Marketplacer</strong><span>One Order and correct Seller Invoice split</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Seller</strong><span>Receipt, fulfilment and tracking</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Finance</strong><span>Commercial and payment reconciliation</span></div></div><h3>Containment controls</h3><div class=\"control-grid\"><article><strong>Customer access</strong><p>Reduce traffic, remove navigation or disable checkout.</p></article><article><strong>Seller and catalogue</strong><p>Pause one Seller, take affected Products offline or remove a Promotion.</p></article><article><strong>Integrations</strong><p>Pause Product sync, Seller Invoice delivery, a Webhook or an integration worker.</p></article><article><strong>Finance</strong><p>Hold remittance or payout while preserving reconciliation access.</p></article></div><div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Containment is not deletion.</strong> Preserve the access and records needed to fulfil open Orders, process returns and refunds, communicate with customers and reconcile Finance.</div>","Conduct the Go or No-Go Review":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Decision</th><th>Use when</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Go</td><td>Blockers are closed, evidence is complete and launch owners are ready.</td></tr><tr><td>Conditional Go</td><td>The remaining risk is isolated, monitored, time-bound and covered by a tested workaround and stop condition.</td></tr><tr><td>No-Go</td><td>Customer, Seller, financial, privacy, security, integration or recovery outcomes remain unsafe.</td></tr></tbody></table></div><h3>No-Go conditions</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list blocker-list\"><li>Payment cannot be reconciled to one recoverable Order.</li><li>Duplicate Orders, payments, refunds or payouts remain possible.</li><li>Customer price, commission or wholesale entitlement is unreliable.</li><li>Wholesale Prices are missing for live Products.</li><li>Sellers cannot receive or fulfil Orders.</li><li>Refunds, remittance or payout cannot be completed and explained.</li><li>Production endpoints or credentials are uncertain.</li><li>Security, privacy or monitoring risk remains.</li><li>No safe containment method exists.</li></ul><p>A No-Go decision protects the marketplace. It is not a project failure.</p>","Operator Production Readiness Checklist":"<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>One Production Readiness register covers the marketplace.</li><li>Launch scope and deferred scope are approved and frozen.</li><li>Production environment, users, credentials and endpoints are verified directly.</li><li>Customer experience and communications pass.</li><li>Every Seller and the launch catalogue are approved.</li><li>Commission, wholesale, tax, fees, refunds, remittance and payout are ready.</li><li>Integrations, monitoring, alerts and reconciliation have owners.</li><li>Support, incident, communication and Marketplacer Support routes are ready.</li><li>Smoke test and containment controls are approved.</li><li>Go, Conditional Go or No-Go is recorded by authorised stakeholders.</li></ul><div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>This page is complete when:</strong> The marketplace has received formal approval to begin the controlled launch.</div><div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Next step:</strong> Continue to <a href=\"?page=go-live\">Go-Live</a>.</div><h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"link-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/26318966306957-Staging-environment-sync\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Staging environment sync</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/28925785268365-Operator-user-role-permissions\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Operator user role permissions</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/31441597254285-Finance-Settings\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Finance Settings</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360052908272-Seller-payments-and-remittance-workflow\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Seller payments and remittance workflow</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/41580327625613-Introduction-to-MPay-for-Operators\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Introduction to MPay</a></li><li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/webhooks/webhookretries/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Webhook Retry Policy</a></li><li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/webhooks/errorsfaults/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Errors and Faults for Webhooks</a></li><li><a href=\"https://changelog.marketplacer.com/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">What’s New on Marketplacer</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/requests/new\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Submit a request</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["testing-strategy","Testing Strategy"],["configuration-testing","Marketplace Configuration Testing"],["catalogue-testing","Catalogue Testing"],["end-to-end-testing","End-to-End Testing"],["seller-launch-readiness","Seller Launch Readiness"],["go-live","Go-Live"],["getting-support","Getting Support"]]},"go-live":{"summary":"Execute the approved marketplace launch in a controlled sequence, monitor the first live activity, contain issues quickly, stabilise the marketplace through hypercare and transition ownership into business-as-usual operations.","audience":["Marketplace leadership","Marketplace operations","Ecommerce","Technology and integrations","Catalogue","Finance","Customer service","Seller management","Commercial","Implementation partners"],"sections":{"Understand Go-Live":"<p>Go-Live is the controlled execution of the approved marketplace launch. Testing and readiness should already be complete. The purpose is to activate the approved scope, observe live activity, contain issues quickly, stabilise operations and hand over to business as usual.</p><div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Approve</strong><span>Record the Go decision and launch scope</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Activate</strong><span>Enable approved Sellers, Products and customer access</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Observe</strong><span>Monitor the first live transactions and operational queues</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Stabilise</strong><span>Resolve launch issues through hypercare</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Handover</strong><span>Transition into business as usual</span></div></div><div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>A live website is not a successful launch by itself.</strong> Customers must be able to transact, Sellers must operate, Finance must reconcile and the Operator must detect and manage issues.</div>","Confirm the Go Decision":"<ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Formal Go approval, launch date, time and time zone.</li><li>Approved Sellers, Products, Categories, regions, commercial models and deferred scope.</li><li>Accepted risks, owners, monitoring and stop conditions.</li><li>Launch team, primary and backup decision-makers and communication channel.</li><li>Customer Service and Support handover.</li><li>Marketplacer Support liaison and escalation route.</li><li>Relevant Marketplacer internal teams notified where required.</li><li>Recent relevant Changelog, Developer documentation, maintenance and platform-status updates reviewed.</li><li>No emergency change has invalidated the Production baseline.</li></ul><div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Do not activate on an informal verbal approval.</strong> Record the decision, approvers, scope, evidence and launch conditions.</div>","Activate the Launch Team":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Role</th><th>Responsibility</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Launch lead</td><td>Runbook, timing, checkpoints and status.</td></tr><tr><td>Marketplace Operations</td><td>Orders, Sellers, fulfilment and queues.</td></tr><tr><td>Ecommerce and Technology</td><td>Storefront, checkout, payments and connected services.</td></tr><tr><td>Catalogue and Seller management</td><td>Products, pricing, stock and Seller operations.</td></tr><tr><td>Finance</td><td>Commercial calculations, refunds and reconciliation.</td></tr><tr><td>Customer Service</td><td>Customer issues, communications and escalation.</td></tr><tr><td>Technical escalation owner</td><td>APIs, Webhooks, MConnect and recovery.</td></tr><tr><td>Marketplacer Support liaison</td><td>Submit evidence-backed requests and coordinate response.</td></tr><tr><td>Executive decision-maker</td><td>Pause, continue, reduce scope or approve emergency change.</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Document who can pause traffic, a Seller, a Product group, an integration, remittance or payout, and who owns customer and Seller communication.</p>","Follow the Launch-Day Runbook":"<p>Use one chronological launch-control log with timestamp, action, owner, expected result, actual result, evidence, issue, decision and next action.</p><div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><div><strong>Reconfirm Go</strong><p>Verify scope, baseline, coverage, support and stop controls.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><div><strong>Activate approved scope</strong><p>Enable Sellers, Products, storefront placement, integrations and Promotions in sequence.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><div><strong>Complete the first transaction</strong><p>Observe every boundary and reconcile the result.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><div><strong>Release limited traffic</strong><p>Expand only after the controlled stage passes.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><div><strong>Operate checkpoints</strong><p>Review Orders, Sellers, catalogue, integrations, customers and Finance.</p></div></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">6</span><div><strong>End-of-day decision</strong><p>Continue, contain, reduce scope or pause.</p></div></div></div>","Activate Approved Sellers and Products":"<ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Activate only Sellers that passed Seller Launch Readiness.</li><li>Publish only the approved Product and Variant assortment.</li><li>Keep deferred, rejected, unmapped, invalid and restricted Products offline.</li><li>Keep Products with missing Wholesale Price, stock, shipping or tax unavailable.</li><li>Confirm correct customer navigation, payment methods and Promotions.</li><li>Confirm Seller users, Order receipt and fulfilment process are active.</li></ul>","Release Traffic in Controlled Stages":"<div class=\"card-grid\"><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Stage 1: Controlled</h3><p>A known participant completes the first Production transaction while the launch team observes.</p></article><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Stage 2: Limited</h3><p>Release a small audience, region, channel, Seller assortment or Product range.</p></article><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Stage 3: Wider</h3><p>Expand only after payment, Orders, Seller receipt, fulfilment, pricing, stock, support and Finance remain stable.</p></article></div><h3>Expansion criteria</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Payment and Marketplacer Order reconcile.</li><li>Seller Invoices reach the correct Sellers.</li><li>Fulfilment and tracking return correctly.</li><li>Prices, Wholesale Prices, stock and shipping remain correct.</li><li>No critical incident is open.</li><li>Customer Service, Seller Support and Finance can manage the current load.</li></ul>","Complete and Monitor the First Live Transaction":"<p>End-to-End Testing owns broad scenario coverage. Go-Live observes the first approved Production execution and decides whether to continue.</p><div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Customer</strong><span>Product, cart, shipping and payment</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Marketplacer</strong><span>One Order and correct Seller Invoice split</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Seller</strong><span>Receipt, fulfilment and tracking</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Customer experience</strong><span>Status and communication update</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Finance</strong><span>Commercial and payment reconciliation</span></div></div><h3>Capture</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Storefront Order ID and payment-provider reference.</li><li>Marketplacer Order ID, Seller Invoice IDs and External IDs.</li><li>Seller-system Order ID.</li><li>Product, Variant, quantity, retail and Wholesale Price where applicable.</li><li>Commercial model, commission or wholesale entitlement.</li><li>Shipment ID, Carrier, tracking and customer communication.</li><li>Finance reconciliation result.</li></ul><div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Stop wider release for a material mismatch.</strong> Examples include wrong price, unrecoverable payment, duplicate Order, wrong Seller, missing Seller Invoice, wrong entitlement, invalid shipping or privacy exposure.</div>","Monitor Marketplace Operations":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Area</th><th>Monitor</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Orders and Sellers</td><td>Payments, Orders, Seller Invoices, receipt, fulfilment, tracking, SLA, cancellations and returns.</td></tr><tr><td>Catalogue</td><td>Products online or offline, Mapping, Catalog Rules, Product Vetting, retail, Wholesale Price, stock and shipping.</td></tr><tr><td>Customer journey</td><td>Search, Product page, cart, checkout, confirmation, Shipment, cancellation, return and refund.</td></tr><tr><td>Integrations</td><td>API errors, uncertain outcomes, delayed or duplicate events, Webhook status, MConnect and queues.</td></tr><tr><td>Finance</td><td>Payments, commission, wholesale margin, fees, tax, refunds, remittance and payout.</td></tr><tr><td>Communications</td><td>Customer, Seller and operational emails, alerts and support volume.</td></tr></tbody></table></div><h3>Integration-specific checks</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Rejected, failed, disabled and skipped Webhooks.</li><li>Retry activity and repeated delivery.</li><li>MConnect Product, Seller Invoice and fulfilment failures.</li><li>Delayed events and queue backlog.</li><li>Seller Invoice delivery failure.</li><li>Unresolved integration exceptions and reconciliation differences.</li></ul>","Manage Launch Issues and Containment":"<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Detect</strong><span>Confirm customer, Seller, Product and financial impact</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Assess</strong><span>Set severity, owner and decision time</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Contain</strong><span>Use the smallest effective control</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Recover</strong><span>Correct the authoritative source</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Reconcile</strong><span>Identify every affected record</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Communicate</strong><span>Update teams, Sellers and customers</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Close</strong><span>Retest, document and approve</span></div></div><h3>Containment examples</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Pause one Seller or Product group.</li><li>Remove one Promotion.</li><li>Pause Product sync or Seller Invoice delivery.</li><li>Disable one Webhook or stop one worker.</li><li>Reduce customer traffic or disable checkout.</li><li>Hold remittance or payout.</li></ul><div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Containment is not deletion.</strong> Preserve access to fulfil existing Orders, process returns and refunds, communicate with customers and reconcile Finance.</div>","Operate Hypercare":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Period</th><th>Cadence</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Activation</td><td>Continuous observation and scheduled checkpoints</td></tr><tr><td>Launch day</td><td>Cross-functional status reviews</td></tr><tr><td>First week</td><td>Daily review</td></tr><tr><td>Following weeks</td><td>Risk-based or twice-weekly review</td></tr><tr><td>First financial cycle</td><td>Dedicated refunds, remittance, payout and accounting review</td></tr></tbody></table></div><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Track incidents, defects, workarounds, Seller questions, customer contacts, Product corrections, integration failures and Finance differences.</li><li>Do not expand scope while the current stage is unstable.</li><li>Keep owners and target dates for every temporary control.</li></ul>","Transition to Business as Usual":"<ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Active Seller, Product, commercial-model and source-of-truth registers.</li><li>Daily Operations, Order, fulfilment, cancellation, return, refund, remittance and payout procedures.</li><li>Integration register, monitoring, alerts and incident runbooks.</li><li>Seller, Customer Service, Finance, technical and Marketplacer Support contacts.</li><li>Known defects, accepted risks, temporary workarounds and deferred scope.</li><li>Reporting, Seller Performance, change-control and support cadence.</li></ul><h3>Hypercare exit criteria</h3><ul class=\"criteria-list\"><li>Orders, Seller Invoice delivery, fulfilment and tracking are stable.</li><li>Customer contacts are manageable.</li><li>Commission and wholesale outcomes reconcile.</li><li>Refunds reconcile.</li><li>First remittance and payout cycle is understood.</li><li>Critical incidents are closed.</li><li>Permanent owners accept the handover and runbooks are current.</li></ul>","Operator Go-Live Checklist":"<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Go decision, scope, accepted risks, team and authority are recorded.</li><li>Production baseline and current Marketplacer updates are reviewed.</li><li>Only approved Sellers and Products are activated.</li><li>Traffic is released in stages.</li><li>First live payment, Order, Seller Invoice, fulfilment, customer communication and Finance result reconcile.</li><li>Orders, catalogue, integrations, customers and Finance have named monitors.</li><li>Webhook and MConnect status, retries, failures and queues are monitored.</li><li>Issues use one containment, recovery and reconciliation process.</li><li>Hypercare cadence, first financial cycle and BAU handover are complete.</li><li>Hypercare exit is formally approved.</li></ul><h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"link-list\"><li><a href=\"https://changelog.marketplacer.com/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">What’s New on Marketplacer</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/requests/new\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Submit a request</a></li><li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/operator-api/examples/orders/howto_order/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Creating Orders</a></li><li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/webhooks/webhookretries/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Webhook Retry Policy</a></li><li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/webhooks/deduplication/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Webhook Deduplication</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/8837682695053-Search-and-find-orders-in-the-Seller-Portal\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Search and find Orders in the Seller Portal</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360040011851-Enable-and-use-the-returns-module\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Enable and use the returns module</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360052908272-Seller-payments-and-remittance-workflow\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Seller payments and remittance workflow</a></li><li><a href=\"https://dev.marketplacer.com/docs/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Marketplacer Developer Documentation</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["testing-strategy","Testing Strategy"],["end-to-end-testing","End-to-End Testing"],["seller-launch-readiness","Seller Launch Readiness"],["production-readiness","Production Readiness"],["operator-dashboard","Operator Dashboard"],["daily-operations","Daily Marketplace Operations"],["seller-performance","Seller Performance"],["integration-troubleshooting","Integration Troubleshooting"],["getting-support","Getting Support"]]}};
